title: kahlua dip
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and cream cheese; blend well. Stir in	 Kahlua.
Chill,
covered,
overnight.	Serve
with sliced, fresh fruit.

title: stay soft chocolate frosting
directions: Blend cocoa, sugar and cornstarch.
Add milk and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and butter.
Stir gently until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: white hot chocolate
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of the half and half or light cream, vanilla baking pieces or chopped candy coating, stick cinnamon and nutmeg in a medium saucepan; whisk over low heat until vanilla baking pieces or candy is melted.

Remove stick cinnamon. Add remaining half and half or light cream. Whisk until heated through. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and almond extract. Serve warm in cups or mugs; top with slivers of vanilla-flavor candy coating and sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired. Makes 5 (6-ounce) servings.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Let stand overnight and put in jars and seal.

title: cherry jubilee salad
directions: Add all ingredients and chill!

title: potato casserole
directions: Place partially thawed hash brown potatoes in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up 1/2 cup butter in small squares and spread over potatoes.
In a large bowl mix chicken soup, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Spread over potatoes and spread with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Melt butter in large casserole.
Cover bottom of dish with a layer of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Add a layer of chicken pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Cover chicken with soup mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia shake
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Cover and brew for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and chill.
In a 5-cup blender, combine tea, pineapple and ice cream until smooth.
If desired, garnish with flaked coconut.
Makes 5 servings.

title: divinity
directions: In small bowl, beat egg whites with salt (speed 7). Transfer egg whites to large bowl. Place on revolving stand. Pour gradually, beating constantly. Pour in fine stream. After all syrup is added, increase speed. Beat until mixture has glossy stage. Add vanilla. Beat at speed 3 until mixture forms peaks. It is ready when tested by dropping teaspoon of hot mixture into a cup of water reaches medium hard-ball stage. Add walnuts or pecans, if desired. Pour into buttered Pyrex dish and cut into squares or drop from teaspoon.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: In a small bowl stir together all ingredients.
Cover and chill to store.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: aunt grace's bananas and peanuts
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add a little oleo and milk or Milnot after cooking.
Roll bananas in mixture, then in chopped nuts.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: In a 20 quart container, put onion and green peppers in 2 gallons water and bring
to
a
rapid boil.
Add meat, tomatoes, beans, beef base, pepper, salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Stir well.	Add
cabbage.
Bring
to
boil	and
then simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: squash or zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter in small baking dish.
Add squash and onion.
Pour mixture over all and bake approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven. Just before removing from oven, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together Bisquick, cheese and pepper. Stir in egg until mix is just moist. Fold in zucchini. Cook "rounds" in skillet until brown.

title: southern pralines
directions: Break
grahams into single cookies.
Place side by side on cookie
sheet.
Put
pecan	on
top
of
each cracker. Boil butter and sugar for 2 minutes. Spoon mixture over grahams and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Take off sheet immediately.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Roll Ritz crackers fine.
Melt butter.
Mix together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; save some cracker mixture for topping.

title: taco dip supreme
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Season with salt and pepper. Place in bottom of glass bowl.
Layer tomatoes and avocados on top of ground beef.
Then layer cheese.
Fold in taco sauce.
Spread sour cream on top.
Serve hot with taco-flavored Doritos.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according
to box and drain.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook
rice as directions on the box. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach.
Squeeze out excess water.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving or overnight.

title: zucchini squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon into 1/2-inch oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's rice soup for whatever ailed you(especially good for flu and stomach upsets)
directions: Brown
whole
onion
in
butter
and very little water. Some salt
may be added.
Add at least a quart more water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and cook about 15 minutes (not more or
less), then add macaroni and another pinch or so of salt; cook
about
10 to 12 more minutes.
Stir often.
Don't leave it.	Add water if needed.
Now, add 2/3 quart of tomato juice. You
cannot
hurry Rice
Soup.
If you don't have 1/2 hour to stand near, don't start to make it.

title: skillet mac and beef
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain. Combine pasta with remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill for at least 8 hours.
Toss well before serving.

title: company salad
directions: Toss, chill, and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie shells generously with pecan pieces. Measure all ingredients into large bowl.
Beat thoroughly and pour over nuts in pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 350° an additional 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: nasturtium butter
directions: Whip together all ingredients, then fold in coarsely chopped nasturtiums. Form into pats and logs and wrap in plastic.
Can be frozen.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle shredded vegetables with salt and let stand 1 hour. Drain mixture if water accumulates.
Combine sugar and other 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil 3 minutes.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture and let stand 3 minutes.
Stir well. Package in plastic freezer bags or containers and freeze.
To serve, remove desired amount and thaw in refrigerator.
Serves 10.

title: lemonade jello
directions: Combine sugar, lemon jello and boiling water.
Add lemonade. Place in freezer to semi-gel.
Whip Cool Whip with jello mixture. Place in Bundt cake size mold.

title: savory pork steaks
directions: In skillet, brown steaks on both sides in shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reserve 1/4 cup of broth; pour remaining broth into skillet.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Sprinkle with basil.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Drain juice and add water to make one cup (to make gravy).
Combine flour and reserved broth; add to pan juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Pour gravy over meat and vegetables.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain raisins, saving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: In microwave bowl mix sugar, margarine, flour and salt, then add milk and flavor to mixture, using a large spoon.
Cook in microwave until filling is thick.
Separate eggs and beat yolk with a spoon and slowly mix in filling.
Pour filling over layer of wafers and bananas.
Add teaspoon of sugar to egg whites and whip until stiff and cook in the oven until topping is brown.

title: cold carrots
directions: Heat everything except carrots in saucepan to dissolve sugar. Pour over carrots; marinate for 48 hours in refrigerator.
You can serve carrots cold or, if you prefer, you can heat them in your microwave.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni caprice
directions: Place 2 cups macaroni in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover with a layer of green beans, a layer of ham and remaining macaroni.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot and slightly browned, at 350°. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken in water. Cut into bite size pieces and return to broth. Add remainder of ingredients except tortillas. Boil for 10 minutes and then add tortillas. Boil until tortillas are soft.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Sift flour and sugar together. Make a well in flour.
Add egg yolks and oil; mix.
Fold in egg whites and add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Bake for 1 hour and 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and all other dry ingredients together, except sugar.
Prepare carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly; beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, dry ingredients, carrots and 3/4 cup pineapple.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly in pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until sides shrink and top springs back when touched.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; decorate with grated orange peel.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Set salt for 3 hours over cucumbers and onions.
Drain and put into large container and add the rest of the ingredients to onion and cucumbers.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: *Ingredients may be to your preference.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pans.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt into a bowl.
Combine sugar, oil, egg, lemon juice, vanilla and lemon peel in a large bowl.
Whisk to blend.
Mix in dry ingredients, apples and pecans.
Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.
If it comes out clean,
muffin is done.
Turn muffins out onto a rack.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: travis house oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart shallow casserole or 6 to 8 individual casseroles.

title: cream cheese pom poms(a holiday cookie tray favorite!)
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water to a boil in a saucepan; add butter and stir until melted.
Add flour and salt all at once, stirring vigorously.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture leaves sides of pan and resembles mashed potatoes, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool about 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, thoroughly beating with a spoon after each addition until smooth. Drop heaping tablespoons of mixture 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Shape in rounds with peak in center.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Place olive oil in hot skillet, saute onions and garlic.
Add chopped mushroom stems and saute.
Add breadcrumbs, parsley and wine.
Lay mushroom caps stem end up in ungreased baking sheet. Heap teaspoon of filling in each mushroom.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Place apples in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry jello over apples.
Combine flour, sugar and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple-jello mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutty numbers
directions: Mix all the ingredients; shape into numbers or letters.
Cover with chopped peanuts.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: kugel-noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over noodles and mix lightly.
Pour into lasagna pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let sit 20 minutes before cutting.

title: little lunch pizzas
directions: Split one English muffin and toast on medium toaster setting. Top each muffin half with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce and 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Put microwavable paper towel on microwavable dinner plate or paper plate.
Put muffin halves on paper towel.
Microwave uncovered on High for 30 to 45 seconds until cheese is melted. Cool about 2 minutes before eating.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
While oven heats, use to melt margarine in a 9-inch square pan.
Blend in mixing bowl 1 cup sugar and baking powder; add milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour the cherries and syrup over flour mixture trying to distribute cherries evenly.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over cherries.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour.

title: pecan clusters
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, brown sugar, sugar and salt.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecan pieces. Beat until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pineapple jello mold
directions: Add boiling water to gelatine (mix well).
Add softened cream cheese while mixture is still hot.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and beat.
Add pineapple (juice and all); beat until smooth.
Put into Bundt mold.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown ground beef with onion and drain. In a large bowl, mix together soup, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in water.
Add hamburger and rice. Mix well.
Wash peppers; remove tops and seeds.
Place in a glass baking dish and fill with stuffing mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes. Top with cheese in the last 10 minutes.

title: ginger beer
directions: Dissolve the yeast in a little warm water with a teaspoon of the sugar.
Place the sugar and chillies, the thin rind of the lemons with the juice in a large pan and pour over them the 3 quarts of boiling water.
Add the cold water when all the sugar has dissolved, and then add the yeast.
Allow to stand for 24 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup with 1 cup of milk.
Place cubed chicken in the bottom of a pan.
Sprinkle Veg-All on top of chicken.
Pour in soup mixture.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot baked layer and bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into bars.
This recipe will serve 15 people.

title: best-ever zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until a toothpick comes out dry when tested.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Cook vegetables 5 minutes or until tender.
Put garlic, paprika, olive oil and a little salt and pepper into the container of the blender, cover and start motor.
Remove the cover and gradually pour in the cooked vegetables.
Replace the cover and blend soup for 10 seconds, or until it is smooth.
Stir into the soup 1 cucumber, cut into tiny dice and the black olives; chill. At serving time, put an ice cube in each plate and pour over it the chilled gazpacho.
Sprinkle the soup liberally with chopped parsley and garnish it with tiny croutons.

title: brownies
directions: Beat the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add the syrup, flour and soda.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt bark in microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and pour over marshmallows, peanuts and cereal (which has been mixed in a large bowl).
Stir well.
Spread out and cut into squares or drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: sunflower shapes
directions: Grind in food mill; cut with cookie cutters.
Chill.
Makes 24.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Store in covered container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water (or to taste).

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Drain and add to rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 45 minutes or put in crock-pot on low for a few hours.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
When completely cool, top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed jalapenos(appetizer)
directions: Drain peppers and slice in half lengthwise; take seeds out. Soften cream cheese in microwave; mix in other ingredients.
Stuff each pepper half.
Place on baking sheet and put in a 350° until the cheese melts.
Great with before dinner drinks!

title: black russian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients; near the end, stir by hand.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake about 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Turn cake onto plate. Poke holes in cake; spoon glaze over warm cake.
Refrigerate immediately.
If wrapped tightly with Saran Wrap and foil, this cake will keep well.
Serve with ice cream.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add 7-Up.
When partially set, add drained pineapple, marshmallows and sliced bananas. Place in large Pyrex dish and congeal.

title: bar b q hash
directions: Boil meat until it comes off the bone.

title: old-fashion vanilla ice cream
directions: Pour Pet milk in a large mixing bowl; add sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cans cold water.
Stir in all ingredients while pouring water. Add vanilla and add table salt (optional).
Stir ingredients well. Pour ingredients into ice cream freezer can.
Place top on container.
Place ice around can and rock salt.
Turn and move ice and rock salt as needed.
Freezing Time:
12 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine well and pour into regular size or miniature muffin pan.

title: weight watchers tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and tortillas and cook in crock-pot or simmer on stove for 1 hour.
Add cheese and tortillas and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: lasagna
directions: In bowl, mix sauce and spices together.
Set aside.

In another bowl, mix Ricotta cheese and eggs. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the sauce, uncooked noodles, Ricotta cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese until pan is full. Top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Layer fruit in bottom of glass bowl.
Combine milk and sour cream; add pudding mixture and beat until well blended.
Spoon over fruit and top with almonds.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon full on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add food coloring and jello. Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Place whole or sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Pour sauce on top. Chill until firm. Top each slice with whipped topping.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored. Combine flour, baking powder and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet cider pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour.
Add cider, water and 2 well beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick and pour into baked pie crust.
Use 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar for meringue and place in oven just until meringue is browned.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in electric skillet. Set temperature at 280°.
Bring mixture to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a saucepan.
Add and warm to spreading consistency, the mushroom soup, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Place broccoli in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Crumble Cheez-Its crackers over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: punch
directions: Put sherbet and frozen juice in punch bowl and add cold ginger ale and 7-Up.
Stir occasionally.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package, then drain. Combine all other ingredients with noodles. Place in baking dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter in mixing bowl; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses. Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon and baking soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture; chill dough.

title: jiffy macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain any excess grease.
Add bouillon cubes and chopped onion.
Add 1 cup of water; cook until onion is tender and bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Continue cooking until all the water is cooked out.
Remove from heat.
Add soup to the meat mixture.
Prepare the macaroni and cheese dinner following directions on box.
Mix with meat and soup mixture.
A little milk can be added if too thick.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until bubbly.

title: fantastic frozen strawberries
directions: Put cleaned berries in a large bowl with sugar.
Mix carefully.
Mix Sure-Jell with 1 cup water and boil 1 minute. Pour over berries and mix carefully.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Put in freezer bags or containers.

title: braised lemon pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper. Combine catsup, water and brown sugar.
Pour over pork chops.
Place a lemon slice on each chop.
Cover tightly and cook slowly on top of range for 45 minutes or until meat is done.

title: french bread sandwich
directions: Cut French bread in half, then into sections.
Spread mayonnaise.
Place a piece of lettuce on each piece, then the filling (turkey, celery and apples mixed with mayonnaise, aji and a little sugar).
On filling, put cubed cranberry sauce and almond slivers.

title: turkey and wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook 2 minutes, until the onion is translucent.
Add water and broth; stir in rice mix and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, until the rice is tender.
Add sherry and boil 1 minute.
Add turkey. Reduce heat to low.

title: evelyn's ham biscuits
directions: Mix together butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire and onion.
Use tiny, day-old party rolls.
Open them and spread mixture on both sides of roll; top each half with a small piece of ham.
Put small piece of Swiss cheese between halves before closing.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 20 to 24 tiny sandwiches.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk. Mix 1/3 cup Pet milk, cake mix, pecans and melted margarine.
Pat 1/2 (or slightly more) of cake mixture in bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven, then sprinkle chocolate chips on top followed by caramel mixture. Place dropfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Bake 18 minutes.
Cool and eat! Enjoy.

title: mincemeat fingers (loaf)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter and eggs, mixing well.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; stir into potato mixture.
Combine buttermilk and soda; add to potato mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cool.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Cook the oleo, brown sugar, curry powder, fruit juice and flour until thick.
Add pecans and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Super with ham, chicken, turkey and roast beef.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Aerate the flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix the oil, water, margarine and cocoa in the microwave for 2 minutes. Dissolve the soda in buttermilk.
Add the cocoa mixture to the flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: orange almond salad
directions: Toss and coat over low heat in Teflon pan until caramel coating sticks to almonds. 1/4 c. slivered almonds, 1 Tbsp.
+ 1 tsp. sugar.

title: noble's sicilian mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil and melted butter 5 to 8 minutes until soft.
Add tomato paste.
Stir until blended.
Add 1 cup wine and stir.
Pour in the 2 cans tomatoes with juices.
Stir in mushrooms and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Add herbs and red pepper.
Simmer until sauce thickens to preferred consistency, adding more wine if you like.
Season with salt and sugar.
Serve hot over chicken or pasta.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts, about 165 calories per cup.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mayonnaise and a spoonful of sour cream.
Shred lettuce on individual plates.
Add some chicken salad.
Then place some grapes and pineapple chunks around the salad.
Great salad.

title: green rice
directions: Prepare rice.
Cook broccoli slightly and drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, saving some cheese for top of casserole.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan uncovered for 30 minutes at 325°.
Freezes well.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare and bake cornbread as directed on pkg. Cool completely and crumble into medium bowl. To the crumbled cornbread, add tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, corn and crumbled bacon. Stir in mayonnaise. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.

title: mom's judy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Add ice cubes; stir until melted.
Let gel in refrigerator until semi-soft.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and pineapple (make sure pineapple has been well drained).
Thoroughly stir and let gel.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Heat fat in skillet.
When hot, add chops.
Move to medium heat and complete browning on both sides, approximately 15 minutes. Place a slice of onion and one pepper ring on each chop.
Place one tablespoon rice in each ring.
Pour tomatoes around meat and add celery.
Place cover on skillet when steaming, about 8 minutes. Remove to low heat and let simmer for 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
While cooking, soften cream cheese and blend in milk, salt and butter or margarine until smooth and creamy. After potatoes are done, drain, mash and add cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce. Stir in all ingredients except red pepper and mesa.
Add red pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir mesa flour into 1/4 cup warm water to make a thick, but flowable, mixture.
Add mesa mixture.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: karrot kake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Drain off 1/4 of the juice from pineapple. Add juice and remaining ingredients to dry ingredients; mix well. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Spread in ungreased, 8-inch square pan or ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, 1/3 stick of butter, white sugar, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl and mix well.
Put mixture in a baking dish.
For topping, combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Mix well and spread over potato mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix until well blended.
Grease 6 (6 x 12-inch) miniature loaf pans.
Evenly distribute batter in each pan.
Bake on middle shelf in the oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until top springs back to the touch.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in liquids over low heat.
Add salad mix and cool.
Pour over sauerkraut and chopped vegetables.
A glass jar is good for storing overnight in refrigerator before serving. Keeps well.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
all together and set aside.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine. Crush
1 stack Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Press into
a
casserole dish (save a few crackers for top).
Pour
in casserole dish and sprinkle a few crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add apples.
Stir until apples are well coated.
Add nuts.
Stir well.
Add well beaten eggs and oil.
Mix with hands when batter is stiff.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour 20 minutes.
If too done, try at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: savory meat loaf and roasted potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 soup, beef, 1/2 can fried onions and Worcestershire sauce thoroughly.
Shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Place potatoes around loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir potatoes, spoon remaining soup over meat loaf.
Bake 25 minutes or until done. Stir potatoes again.
Sprinkle on remaining onions over meat. Bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Serves 8.

title: peachy pecan bread
directions: Drain peaches reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Chop peaches and reserve 1 cup of peaches.
In a blender, puree the rest of peaches along with butter, eggs and lemon juice.
In a bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; combine this to the pureed peaches. Fold in the reserved peach pieces and nuts.
Pour mix into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch greased pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Spread with peach preserves and cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to rack.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, but poppy seed.
Add water as needed; stir in poppy seed.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Boil the peaches until tender. Cut 1 stick butter up and place on the bottom of baking dish. Blend flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt. Pour batter over butter. Bake at 350° until batter turns golden brown.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour soda and boiling water over dates and raisins. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar. Add vanilla, then egg.
Beat well. Add flour and mix.
Pour in fruit mixture (including water) and nuts.
Mix.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk and let cool. Sift together sugar and flour.
Beat eggs.
Add butter and potatoes, milk and yeast mixture.
Add liquid to dry mixture.
Mix 1 hour before baking.
Knead and shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 450 degrees for 12-15 minutes.

title: pork and spinach pie
directions: Place pie shell on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 325°.
Spread cheese on bottom of shell and set aside.
In a skillet, brown sausage; drain off fat.
Stir in stuffing mix and spinach; spoon over cheese.
Beat together eggs and milk and pour over sausage in pie shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with your favorite chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat. Grease a 13 x 9 pan. Then layer most of the croutons, cheese and sausage in the pan. Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups of milk and mustard. Pour mixture over ingredients in pan. Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown and white sugar, flour, salad oil, nutmeg and salt.
Take from this mixture approximately 1 cup.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and chopped nuts.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Pour into mixing bowl and let cool.
Then add sugar to mixture.
Add egg.
Sift flour once, measure into sifter and add salt.
Slowly add flour mixture and 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Mix soda with 1/4 cup of milk; add to mixture along with vanilla.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip potatoes and other ingredients with beater and place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with water and soak over night.
Drain off water and add fresh water until it is about 2 inches above beans.
Add tasso or ham hocks, onion and bell
pepper and cook until beans are tender.
Remove 1 cup beans and mash.
Add mashed beans, bay leaves and sausage back to the pot and cook for 15 minutes.
Add Tony's, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar until light; blend in banana and egg until creamy. Stir in Bisquick, nutmeg and nuts just until moistened. Do not over mix. Put into greased 9 x 5 x 3 pan or 4 small pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or 30 minutes for small pans. Cool in pan 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: jalapeno cake
directions: Mix together and spread thin layer on each tortilla. Stack layers and cover with cream cheese.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks.
Add remaining ingredients (flour, lemon juice, lemon rind and milk).
After thoroughly mixed, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch). Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until firm in center.

title: onion and fennel soup au gratin
directions: In 1 quart nonstick saucepan, melt margarine; add onions and fennel.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until onions are translucent, about 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water, the dissolved broth mix and pepper; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer until flavors blend, about 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: You can use strawberries, peaches, blueberries, cherries or pineapple.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no stick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in spread; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix fruit, then mix juice and pudding mix (if mixture is too thick, add either fruit juice or water).
Pour mixture over fruit and chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine by hand to make crumbs. Set aside 2 cups of the crumbs.
Mix boiling water, corn syrup and baking soda.
Stir into the crumbs.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the 2 cups of crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 4-star chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter or shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend 1/2 cup cocoa into 1/3 cup water and add to first mixture.
Add alternately to the mixture the sifted flour, cold water and vanilla.
Fold in 3 egg whites, beaten stiff with 3/4 cup sugar added.
Add to cake mixture gradually.
Add last the soda, mixed in 1 tablespoon boiling water.
Bake in loaf or layer pans in a 350° oven.

title: two season squash medley
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter and oil over medium heat. Add vegetables, garlic and thyme. Cook and stir until tender, about 15 minutes. Add garlic salt and pepper.

title: lynn's famous tater tot casserole
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Combine ground beef, Cheez Whiz and chicken soup; pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover the top with the Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with garlic salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to 310°.
Remove from heat.
Add oil and coloring. Stir. Pour onto buttered pan. Cut in small pieces. Drop in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice.
Melt butter.
Add onions or onion soup mix.
Stir in creamed soups and Velveeta cheese.
After cheese has melted, stir in broccoli.
Add to cooked rice in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix well and cook for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli; drain.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake until bubbly at 350°, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dice eggs into small cubes.
Combine chicken, celery, salt, pepper and eggs with mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Garnish with olives.
Chill and serve.

title: hot texan cake
directions: Bring water, cocoa and margarine to a boil.
Add cocoa mixture to flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon mixture and blend.
Add vanilla, eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Beat altogether and put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden chicken
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
Pour on a buttered floured pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: orange-lemonade
directions: Squeeze oranges and lemons.
Put juice in 2-quart pitcher. Add water to make 2 quarts.
Slice used orange and lemon halves into quarters.
Add to juices.
Add sugar to taste.
Serve cold, with mint sprigs in each glass.

title: lasagna swirls(serves 8)
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix ingredients together then spread about 1/4 cup of mixture along length of noodle.
Roll it up and stand on end in a greased 2 1/2 deep casserole dish.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Boil squash for 10 to 15 minutes in salted water.
Brown ground beef.
Split squash lengthwise; rake out the middle of squash.
Combine meat, onions, celery, bread crumbs, middle of squash and cheese together.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in squash shells with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrot and chicken stock or water and simmer about 1 hour.
Add beans, parsley and sweet basil and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook any kind of small macaroni separately.
Drain pasta.
Mix together with beans.
Add Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Good luck.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and cook 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 6 tablespoons juice.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift flour with salt, soda and spices.
Mix with oatmeal and add to first mixture alternately with raisin liquid.
Add raisins and nut meats.
Drop on greased baking sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add water.
Mix next 4 ingredients into
a crumb-like texture.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are done. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend. Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast in warm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
When ready to bake, roll out and place on greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Stir corn meal in rapidly boiling water.
Cover and cook over boiling water 45 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cook garlic, onion and green pepper in oil until tender; add meat and cook until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour layer of corn meal mixture into greased baking dish; cover with meat mixture; top with rest of corn meal mixture and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan with more than half of the wafer crumbs. Cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Spread over crumbs. Crush and sweeten berries and spread next. Top with whipped topping, then with remaining crumbs. Chill overnight.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in oleo until limp, not brown.
Add onions to other ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Top with slice of French bread and cheese.

title: brunch eggs(18 to 20 servings)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Heat soup enough to smooth.
Add sherry, mushrooms, green pepper and pimento.
Scramble eggs in butter until softly firm.
Put in buttered 3-quart casserole. Layer eggs, soup mixture and cheese; repeat.
Dash with paprika. Put in cold oven; turn heat to 250°.
Bake for 1 hour or until hot.
Can be prepared the day before and refrigerated before baking.

title: two-cheese seafood linguini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
While pasta is cooking, cook garlic and oregano in butter in a saucepan, stirring frequently, for about 1 minute.
Add chopped tomato and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes or until tomato is cooked through.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until Blue cheese is melted and sauce is hot.
Place hot-cooked pasta on a serving dish and top with sauce.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9 inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Spray a 1-inch side pan (jelly roll or cookie sheet).
Brown beef, vegetables and spices in skillet.
As soon as vegetables are wilted and meat loses red color, add the soups and grated Parmesan cheese.
Cook 15 minutes.
Prepare macaroni according to directions.
Drain and air dry.
Beat together milk and egg.
Stir into macaroni and spread in pan (greased).
Cover with beef and tomato mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let set and cut into 8 large squares.

title: cornflake "macaroons"
directions: Beat egg white, gradually adding 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Stir in remaining 6 tablespoons sugar and other ingredients.
Place by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: coney island sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook the meat, crumbling with a fork until it loses its red color.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring constantly for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: beef with peppers
directions: Heat pan; add oil and garlic (crushed).
Add beef, cut in small thin strips.
Brown.
Add salt, pepper and soup stock; simmer a few minutes.

title: devil's food cake with chocolate frosting
directions: Spray two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans with nonstick coating and dust lightly with flour; set pans aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 3/4 cups sugar, cocoa powder and baking soda.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed about 30 seconds or until combined. Beat on medium to high speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of the bowl occasionally.
Thoroughly wash the beaters.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the egg whites until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Gradually add the 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Fold into the batter.
Pour the batter into the prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool cakes in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove cakes from pans and cool them thoroughly on wire racks. Spread the Chocolate Frosting between the layers, then frost sides and top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and salt; add in fourths to butter mixture, blending well.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut out 2-inch circles (or other shapes).
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Make a thumbprint about 1/4-inch deep in each cookie.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 13 minutes, or until delicately browned on edges.

title: chinese sparerib sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and brush on cooked ribs.
Broil for 5 minutes; turn ribs over and repeat.
Use the remaining sauce as a dip when serving.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and nuts.
Press in bottom of 9x15 inch dish.
Bake in slow oven until brown.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip together.
(If too stiff, add milk.) Spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Put this on top of cream cheese layer.
Add other 1/2 container of Cool Whip; sprinkle with about 1/2 c. nuts. Chill for several hours.
Serves 12.

title: sweet potato pecan casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, mix together the sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, vanilla, milk and nutmeg until the mixture is smooth.
Transfer to lightly buttered 2-quart baking dish.
In a bowl, stir together the brown sugar, flour, remaining butter and pecans.
Sprinkle the mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cornflakes with butter.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Put shredded cabbage on top of cornflake mix.
Combine milk, cheese, mayonnaise and soup; pour over cabbage.
Top with remaining cornflake mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream frozen dessert
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in milk.
Turn into freezing tray and freeze 3/4 to 1 hour (until slushy).
Whip cream until stiff. Add partially frozen Kool-Aid mixture to whipped cream and whip just enough to mix well, but keep as cool as possible.
Return quickly to freezing tray and freeze at coldest point, with no more stirring.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in hot milk.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix well. Add squash, salt and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs and pour in greased baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: heavenly fudge
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients until no traces of milk powder or cocoa remain.
Turn mixture into an individual loaf pan or a 10 ounce custard cup and place in freezer until firm. Makes 1 serving.
Calories per serving:

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Apply evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish the potatoes and 1 tablespoon of onions.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/8 teaspoon of pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix ground beef, milk, cracker crumbs, catsup, 1/4 cup onions, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are tender (50 to 60 minutes).
Serves 4 large helpings.

title: quick whole wheat bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Dissolve the sugar in lukewarm water.
Stir into the yeast and leave in a warm place for 10 to 15 minutes until frothy.
In a large bowl, mix the flour with the salt and rub in the margarine. Beat the yeast liquid into the flour to form a dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead by folding the dough toward you, then pushing away with the palm of the hand for about 10 minutes, until firm and elastic.
Place the dough in bowl.
Cover with lightly oiled polythene and leave to rise until double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours in warm place).
Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead for about 2 minutes until firm.
Shape to fit a lightly greased 450-g/1-pound loaf pan; cover with oiled polythene and leave in a warm place for about 45 minutes until the dough is just rounded over the top of the pan.
Heat the oven to 450°.
Bake the loaf for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown and sounds hollow if tapped underneath.
Cool on a wire tray.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour; mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon the pie filling onto the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden.
Filling will sink into the cake while baking.
Cut into 16 pieces to serve.
Dust with powdered sugar and spoon slightly sweetened whipped cream over each serving. Great served warm!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole about 1 hour at 350° or less time if meat is boneless.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Blend for 1 minute, the eggs, Bisquick, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Add remaining ingredients and push under with a spoon.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easter ham
directions: Score or puncture ham with knife or meat fork.
Place pineapple rings around on top.
Place cherries in center of rings. Secure with cloves.
(May need toothpicks too if skin is thick.) Make a mixture of pineapple juice and cherry juice.
Add handful of brown sugar.
Heat slightly until sugar dissolves and pour over ham.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, less it heats thoroughly.
May use Brown-in-Bag.
It really keeps the moisture in!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pork chops ol
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops on both sides in oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, combine rice, water, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Arrange chops over rice; top with green pepper.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours or until meat juices run clear.
Uncover; Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields:
4 - 6 servings.

title: awesome applesauce brownies
directions: Melt butter, sugar and chocolate in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, applesauce and vanilla; mix well.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine and pour into 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Dab butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar on bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
In large mixer bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream and flour mix; blend well.
Add oats, raisins and nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Drop on cookie sheet by spoonful.
Keeps for a long time (maybe).

title: 5 in 1 salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf with Ritz crackers.

title: valentine red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Mix flour, cocoa and baking powder together.
Add eggs into sugar, margarine and Crisco, one at a time.
Add flour and milk to mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into pan. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°, usually 2 hours.

title: five-cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and allow to stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Standing overnight is best.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save 1 cup broth.
Pull chicken off bone.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Blend next 7 ingredients in blender. Add to spinach; mix.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with chicken or pork.

title: lemon dessert
directions: This recipe has an interesting true story with it.
While I was chaperoning the mass media class on their annual trip to New York City, we went to lunch at Planet Hollywood.
Two of us decided to eat light so we would have room to share a dessert.
The White Chocolate Bread Pudding sounded good so that is what we ordered. Well, let me tell you, after one bite, I was sure I made a mistake, I should have ordered one by myself.
It was the best dessert I have ever tasted, not real sweet, just out of this world. Grrreat!!!
While devouring mine slowly, a man came to our table to ask our opinion of the food.
We told him how good it was and asked him if he worked here.
He told us he was the manager.
Well, you can guess what we asked him next - Could we get the recipe for this dessert?
He said he'd try.
Five minutes passed and he returned with this recipe.
We were so happy to get the recipe, little did I realize it was set up to serve a restaurant.
I'm sure if you have the time to work with this recipe and break it down to feed less, you will not be sorry.
I know I wasn't.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and apricots.
In 9 x 13-inch pan cut peaches and apricots in small chunks.
Stir in strawberries.
Stir in orange juice.
Add lemon juice.
Slice bananas into mixture.
Put fruit salad into a couple of containers and put into freezer.
Before eating, thaw until just barely crunchy.
If thawed completely, it will be too soupy.

title: old time spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cream margarine with sugar and egg.
Add yeast and water to the mixture.
Mix in flour one cup at a time to make a spongy batter.
(An electric mixer works fine.) Place in airtight container and refrigerate until ready to use.
To bake, preheat oven to 450°.
Place heaping tablespoonful of the dough into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
This mixture will keep up to 5 days in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a buttered glass casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and onion.
Mix lightly.
Stir in milk and dot with butter.
Cook, covered, 15 to 18 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Rest, covered, for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top and garnish with paprika or parsley flakes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Clean seeds; discard fiber.
Wash seeds.
Place in shallow layer in roasting pan and roast in a 250° oven until golden brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix all
together; put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: oreo cookie ice cream cake(grandchildren's special)
directions: Put Oreos in a plastic bag and crush into crumbs with a rolling pin.
Spread half the Oreo crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread softened ice cream over Oreo crumbs.
Top with remaining Oreo crumbs.
Chill until set.
Before freezing, you can drizzle with chocolate syrup.
When serving, you can offer choices of hot fudge, whipped cream, cherries, nuts - the gooier the better!

title: jane's sweet dough(mix today and bake tomorrow.)
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Combine in a saucepan milk, water, and margarine and heat to very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients and beat.
Add eggs and more flour to make stiff dough.
Cover with plastic wrap and towel. Set aside 30 minutes.
Mold in your desired shape, round loaf or try braiding.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avery's best ever rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450° for 10 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Slowly add boiling water.
When almost dissolved, add the cup of cold water.
When this mixture is lukewarm, add the yeast and allow to dissolve.
Add beaten eggs, flour and salt; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter, fold over and rebutter.
Place in warm place 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°. Cool about 15 minutes.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix Jell-O with water. Pour over cake.
Chill 3 hours.
Frost with lite Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Blend baking mix and milk.
Turn onto a flour dusted surface and knead about 10 times.
Pat or roll 1/4 inch thick rectangle shape, 8 x 14-inches.
Spread with soft butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll as you would jelly rolls.
Cut 1 inch pieces.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Turn oven on at 425°.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 rolls.

title: chicken fold overs
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Separate 1 large can biscuits to 20 pieces.

title: walnut garlic linguine
directions: Heat oil, garlic and walnuts in skillet over medium heat. Stir until walnuts are lightly toasted.
About 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cook pasta and drain.
Add pasta, parsley, salt, cheese and basil to walnut mixture.
Toss and Serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips, cheese and almonds.
Place in large square or rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: In a saucepan, saute the mushrooms with the butter.
Add the mushroom soup and heat to a boil.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: squash relish
directions: Chop first 6 vegetables fine.
Mix well and add 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Mix salt with vegetables.
Bring sugar, vinegar, water and mustard and celery seed in cloth and let stand alone while vegetables are sitting.
Drain vegetables and add to liquid.
Boil 25 to 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, catsup and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart dish, alternate meat and cheese.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab and corn soup
directions: Shred crab meat.
Mix corn with chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Stir in crab meat and sherry.
Gradually stir in beaten egg yolks.
Mix cornstarch with water and stir into soup.
Bring to a boil constantly.
Beat egg whites and fold into soup.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and water together; set aside to cool.
Cream the butter, sugars and eggs.
Add the flour, cinnamon and soda.
Mix in oatmeal mixture.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine the dry ingredients and set them aside. Cream together the remaining ingredients. Add the dry ingredients half at a time. Stir in chocolate chips. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Combine egg and milk in bowl; add to dry ingredients.
Stir lightly with fork.

title: cantaloupe pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Cook 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Line bowl with wafers; top with sliced cantaloupe.
Pour some custard over cantaloupe; continue layers, ending with wafers. Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: graham cracker cream pie
directions: Combine graham crackers, softened butter, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Pat into a 9-inch pie plate, reserving 1/4 cup for topping.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning; simmer 10 minutes.
Spread refried beans on bottom of the pie crust; add the seasoned meat.
Spoon taco sauce over the meat; sprinkle tomatoes and chopped onions over the sauce.
Cover with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tomatoes in halves.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and press on top of tomato halves.
In shallow baking dish, bake tomatoes until softened, about 15 to 25 minutes (time will depend on firmness of tomatoes).
Topping should be lightly browned.
If not, tomatoes may be placed under broiler.
Makes 4 servings.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in pan over medium heat. Stir only until sugar is dissolved. Cook until a little tried in cold water forms a soft ball (236° to 238°). Beat egg whites on high speed until stiff. Continue beating and pouring in 1/2 of the syrup. Continue beating while cooking the rest of the syrup until it forms a hard ball when tried in cold water. Pour rest of syrup in egg white mixture and continue beating. Add vanilla and nuts. Continue beating by mixer or beat by spoon until candy is thick enough to drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in ice water for about 1/2 hour.
Drain well and cover with buttermilk 1/2 to 1 hour.
Take out of milk and place on paper towel.
Heat oil (I use vegetable oil with 1 tablespoon margarine).
Dredge chicken in flour with salt and pepper.
Fry to your satisfaction or doneness.
Place lid on skillet for about 10 minutes at end of frying (optional).
Drain on paper towel or as is.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Slice
and brown meat. Add vinegar, water, brown sugar, salt, soy
sauce	and pineapple juice. Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until meat is tender. Blend cornstarch in 1/2
cup water. Stir into meat mixture and cook until clear and
thickened. Add
pepper,
onion
and
pineapple.
Cook
2 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater; turn to speed 2 and mix 30 seconds.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Turn to speed 4 and mix 30 seconds.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture on stir speed, 2 minutes.
Increase to speed 2 for 30 seconds.
Add chocolate chips on stir speed for 15 seconds.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Crush the Post Toasties in a low flat bowl.
Pour the evaporated milk in another.
Dip the pork chops in milk, then in the crushed Post Toasties.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook on a lightly greased cookie sheet for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: cheesy cauliflower italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
In a greased casserole dish, layer 1/2 of each in the following order:
cauliflower, onion, flour mixture, butter pieces, olives, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering with second half of ingredients, adding parsley after olives. Sprinkle with paprika.
Combine wine and milk.
Pour over and bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and golden.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Separate rolls in a baking pan, making sure dough sticks together and there are no holes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed, horseradish and chopped scallions.
Spread mixture over crust.
Chop finely any fresh vegetables.
Sprinkle on top cream cheese.
Pat lightly. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut to serve.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membranes. Precook green pepper cups in boiling salted water for about 5 minutes; drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.)
Sprinkle inside of cups generously with salt.

title: bavarian sausage skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, saute coleslaw mix and carrots until crisp tender.
Add water, bring to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients and return to a boil.
Cook for 8 minutes or until noodles are tender stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with caraway seeds if desired.
Approx. 5 servings.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet, stirring to crumble; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine ground beef and all remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream.
Pour into a greased 9 1/2 x 15-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream over top; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: deep dish apple crisp
directions: Prepare
apples by peeling and slicing as you would for a regular pie in a large pie plate.
Use enough apples to fill the plate.
For
topping,
beat 2 eggs, add sugar and butter. Beat well.
Fold
in
flour which has been sifted with baking powder and
salt.
Add
vanilla.
Spread mixture over apples, and bake in a 350° oven until done (about 45 minutes).

title: mock sausage patties
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in medium size bowl and blend well with hands.
Beat egg white with fork and add to mixture; mix with hands.
Shape into 12 patties.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from broiler for 4 to 5 minutes until light brown on nonstick cookie sheet. Turn and broil 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine.
Pour cool water over linguine and let drain again.
Mix ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: smoked sausage roll-ups
directions: Heat sausage links through but not to boiling point.
Drain; let cool as they can be handled with fingers to roll up.
Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place warm sausage on each strip of dough and roll up to the opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with mustard or ketchup.
Makes 48 snacks.
Kids love these and are easy to fix.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomatoes and onion in large bowl.
Add kidney beans and hamburger.
Crush Doritos chips and add to salad.
Pour dressing over and add cheese.
Toss before serving.

title: turkey and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to medium heat. Combine wild rice, brown rice and 5 cups of chicken broth and cook until done. In a large bowl, toss rice, turkey and mushrooms. Add cream, butter, chestnuts, extra chicken broth, onion and garlic with salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a baking dish and sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Bake for about an hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Boil celery, onion and bouillon until tender. Add rest of ingredients and simmer. Thicken with cornstarch.

title: sausage onion squares
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown; drain.
Mix Bisquick, milk and 1 egg.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex pan.
Top with sausage mixture.
Mix sour cream, salt, pepper and 1 egg.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. When cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken keiv
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan melt butter.
Combine crumbs, cheese and spices.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in crumbs.
Place skin side up in a baking dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Add wine, green onions and parsley to remaining butter (about 1/2 cup).
When chicken is golden, pour butter sauce mixture over chicken and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together ingredients; chill overnight.
Roll into balls. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 50 Spinach Balls.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Mix all but bananas.
Process bananas and a little juice in blender.
Add remaining juice and freeze.

title: corn relish
directions: To prepare corn, remove husks and silk.
Place in boiling water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove; plunge into cold water. Drain; cut corn from cob.
Do not scrape the cobs.
Combine all ingredients, except mustard and flour.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Mix mustard and flour.
Blend with water as for gravy.
Add to corn mixture.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pack into hot, sterile jars.
Seal at once.
Yield:
approximately 6 pints.

title: orange candy slice cake and icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 1 cup buttermilk, beat well, add soda to other 1/2 cup buttermilk and add to mixture.
Combine dry ingredients; add orange slice halves, add dates and nuts; blend. Line a tube pan with well-greased brown paper.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Stir flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients together in separate bowl and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease jelly roll pan and line with waxed paper.
Spread batter into pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn upside down onto a confectioners sugar-covered dish towel.
Remove waxed paper immediately and roll up in towel.
Cool completely.

title: wedding noodles
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add noodles.
Bring to a boil again. Take off burner.
Stir 2 to 3 times during forenoon.
(Start as soon as they start seating guests.)

title: all american dinner
directions: Drive to McDonalds and stop at first window.
Say, "I would like 2 cheeseburgers, 2 large French fries and 2 large Dr. Peppers," then drive to second window and pay the person at that window.
Finally, drive to third window and pick up food.

title: petite pizza
directions: Mix together and spread on thinly sliced French rolls.
Place under broiler until bubbly.
Watch carefully as they burn easily. Serve immediately.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli and place in 9 x 13 pan. Add cooked chicken and stir. In a saucepan, heat soup and cheese, stirring until melted. Stir mayonnaise into the soup mixture. Pour the soup mixture over the chicken and sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix the bread crumbs and melted butter in a small bowl and pour over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: okra and rice dish
directions: Place okra, rice, water and salt in pot; cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn into greased baking dish; add tomato sauce.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven. Yields 4 servings.

title: rice pudding(top of range)
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and butter; cook on medium heat until thickened about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add vanilla and pour into serving dish.

title: aunt jennie's chicken
directions: Slice each breast in 2 thin layers.
Wet, then dip each piece in bread crumbs and fry in butter or oil just until crisp on each side.
Lay chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients that are left and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake until sauce thickens, about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Add all the other ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: paul's watercress salad
directions: Wash and cut stems off watercress.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in sour cream (do not defrost peas).
Garnish with sliced avocado and sprinkle of paprika. Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts; mix well to distribute evenly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen cookies.

title: kasha
directions: Bring water to boil in a pot; cook the bow ties.
Drain and cool.
Put kasha in a wide mixing bowl; add the beaten egg.
Mix with a fork until the egg is fully absorbed and all of the grains of kasha are slightly moistened.
Let this mixture dry overnight, or place in a skillet over moderately high heat and stir the kasha until it is dry and the grains separate from each other.
In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil and saute the onions and mushrooms until they are light brown and soft.
Bring 2 cups salted water to a boil in a large pot.
Add the kasha; cook until the kasha has absorbed all of the water.
Mix in the sauteed vegetables and bow ties.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well; add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Fold in finely chopped apples and vanilla. Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans which have been greased well and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chess squares(oh-so-good)
directions: Mix the ingredients together well and pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed lightly with butter-flavored Pam.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together (using an electric mixer) the sugar, shortening, eggs and salt in a large mixing bowl. While continuing to mix, add the milk and the nutmeg and then add sifted flour, baking soda and baking powder.

title: chicken breast with vegetables
directions: Cut chicken and vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Put 3 tablespoons of soy sauce and cornstarch over chicken and let stand for 1 hour.
Fry chicken in 3 tablespoons of oil for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix Jell-O, pecans, coconut, condensed milk and vanilla. Shape mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll chilled berries in red sugar. Dye slivered almonds for stems.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well to dissolve. Add cherry pie mix.
Stir and chill.
While this is setting, prepare the following:
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Meanwhile, beat cream cheese with salad dressing.
Fold into lightly thickened lemon Jell-O along with whipped cream and crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Then add miniature marshmallows. Pour over cherry layer and allow to set overnight.
Put into square cake pan.

title: calico beans - old settlers beans
directions: Drain beans.
Save bean liquid and use if necessary as beans bake.
Brown bacon, ground meat and onion; drain off any fat.
Mix together brown sugar, catsup, vinegar or dry mustard.
Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350° or 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain and place in casserole.
Cook rice according to directions on package; place in casserole with broccoli.
Saute onions in butter.
Blend onions and soup into casserole.
Add salt and pepper and the dash of milk.
Place cheese into casserole; cover with cracker crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into pan and refrigerate.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with saltwater; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook about 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Peel and coarsely shred potatoes.
Set aside.
Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Combine potatoes, cheese mixture, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Spoon into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Pour mixture over Crispix cereal.
Put powdered sugar in a grocery bag.
Put in cereal mixture and shake vigorously.
Enjoy.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Let cream cheese soften and mix with marshmallow cream and flavoring.
This is delicious with any fruit.

title: mary's chicken delight
directions: First boil chicken, then drain and separate.
Keep 1 cup of broth.
Melt margarine in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Put a layer of dressing and then chicken.
Pour cream of chicken soup (undiluted) on top.
Layer again with dressing and chicken and then cream of celery soup (undiluted).
The last layer should be dressing.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sugar glazed walnuts
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High for 1 more minute.
Add nuts and mix to coat. Microwave at High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread nuts onto wax paper and cool slightly.
Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: red velvet gabriella cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix with eggs, oil, buttermilk, cocoa and food coloring. Beat together. Do not add ingredients on cake box. Bake according to cake box instructions. Frost with canned cream cheese frosting.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Put barbecue sauce evenly over the meat.
Put 1 tablespoon brown sugar on each chop.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serve on rice using the sauce cooked with the meat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
In casserole, layer beans, sauce and water chestnuts.
Repeat layers.
Top with slivered almonds. Bake in moderate oven for 1/2 hour.

title: spiced tea(serves 30)
directions: Mix well and store in closed jar.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Blend with fork the cream cheese, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add onions (a little sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed may be added, if desired).
Add chopped chicken last. Form a ball.
Cover with about 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in ungreased casserole dish. Combine soup, salad dressing, margarine, egg and onion.
Mix well. Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle top with cheese and crackers. Press into casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until top is brown.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp barbecue
directions: Wash and clean shrimp well, but do not shell.
Place shrimp in large pan that is at least 2-inches deep.
Melt butter; add to it the pepper, garlic and lemon juice.
Pour this over shrimp.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Turn oven off and let shrimp marinate in warm oven until ready to serve.
Serve shrimp in liquid mixture with green salad and French bread.
Be sure to dip the bread in butter sauce!

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender but not brown.
Stir in beans, bacon and remaining ingredients.
Combine well.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter and sour cream; add egg.
Combine flour, thyme, salt and baking powder and add to first mixture.
