Mix thoroughly. Pour in greased baking dish.
Saute onion, carrots, pepper and mushrooms in margarine; add chicken and soup.
Spread over top of dough and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange marmalade bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in orange peel.
Beat egg; add milk, marmalade and butter.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Let stand 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tests done.

title: irish fruit soda bread
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a saucepan, including juice from pineapple.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 10 minutes, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Into a large mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients and spices.
Add cooled raisin mixture and eggs.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full with sliced, peeled apples.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle over apples.
Mix the last 4 ingredients well and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt marion's hawaiian short ribs
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Mix the flour with two tablespoons salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge ribs in the flour mixture.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet; add ribs and brown on all sides. Transfer the ribs to a roasting pan, placing them in a single layer.
Sprinkle with sliced onions.
Combine the catsup, water, vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, chili powder and remaining salt and pepper.
Pour over the short ribs and onions. Cover and bake for three hours or until the ribs are very tender. Carefully skim off all traces of fat.
Serve ribs with noodles or rice.
Serves five.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except corn, butter, salt and pepper. When the other ingredients are almost done, add corn and other ingredients to taste.

title: sugar-free bavarian cream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup 2% sweet milk and 1 box sugar-free instant vanilla pudding.
Add the coconut and Cool Whip to first mixture; mix well.
Put into a graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight or for several hours.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: In a double boiler, melted almond bark.
Stir in peanut butter and remove from heat to cool slightly.
Stir in peanuts; mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies and marshmallows; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper until set.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Bring first three to a boil.
Add 1 cup self-rising flour; mix and press in pie pan.

title: morning eye opener
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with fork just until thoroughly combined.
Pour into tall glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well each time.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Put cornflakes in a bag with the rosemary and pepper and use a rolling pin to crush and mix them together.
Remove all skin from chicken, rinse and dry pieces thoroughly.
Dip in milk; roll in cornflake crumbs.

title: tortoni - an italian delight
directions: Separate eggs.
Turn each white into small bowl of electric mixer.
Refrigerate yolks.
Let whites warm to room temperature 1 hour.
Mix 1/4 cup water with sugar in 1-quart saucepan, stirring over low heat to dissolve.
Boil uncovered without stirring to 236° on candy thermometer (syrup spins 2-inch thread when dropped from spoon).

title: my own weird cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Take 2 bananas and 1 each of lemonade and orange juice and put in blender for mixing.
Repeat till bananas, orange, and lemonade are well mixed.
Add pineapple juice, then sugar and boiling water mixture.
Pour into 3 containers for freezing.
When ready to serve, add each frozen portion to one
32 oz. 7-Up.

title: old fashioned pancakes
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Combine and sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Stir in soured milk, egg and melted butter.
Fry small patties.

title: banana split pie
directions: Make a graham cracker crust, using finely crushed crackers, margarine and sugar.
Line a 10-inch pie plate, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs for garnish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Add onion, and bell pepper to pork and beans. In a bowl, mix together brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and worcestershire sauce. Then mix with pork and beans in big pyrex pan. Put bacon slices on top. Bake at 550 until brown.

title: president's choice (aunt helen's chicken)
directions: Cut chicken into serving size pieces; brown in oil.
Remove to casserole dish.
Add onion to hot oil; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in shallow casserole pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over butter.
Place peaches on top of butter.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Blend gelatin and cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cut roll of cookie dough into 9 slices and then quarter the slices.
Place in an ungreased miniature cupcake tin to form a cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place one peanut butter cup in the center.
Cool and then remove from pan.
Refrigerate.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: bavarian brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, oleo, milk and egg.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Crush crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Spray Dutch oven or casserole dish with non-stick cooking spray. Crumble ground beef in bottom, then slice potatoes in 1/4 inch slices and spread over ground beef. Chop onions and sprinkle on top of potatoes. Add mixed vegetables. In a bowl, mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and vegetable soup. Stir and pour over all ingredients in Dutch oven. Bake at 375 or 400 degrees until potatoes are tender. If casserole starts to get dry, add a little water to finish baking.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together, then add 4 c flour 1 tsp soda and 1 tsp cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll in balls.
Press with a glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°for 10 minutes.

title: budget stretcher
directions: Boil water, onions, tomatoes and seasoning until onions are tender.
Add spaghetti and cook until tender.
(Better second day!)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together through the evaporated milk. Pour into 9 x 13 inch plan.
Mix 1 yellow cake mix and one cube margarine together so it is crumbly.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2
hours or until knife comes out clean.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Very moist.
Serves 15.

title: soft taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef in 10-inch skillet on stove top, breaking into dime-size or smaller pieces; drain well.
Stir in seasoning mix and 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Simmer for 4 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in Salsa Con Queso thoroughly.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Melt margarine in pot.
Mix flour, raisins, sugar, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Add margarine, beaten eggs and buttermilk; mix with spoon.
Form in a ball and pat to cake size on baking sheet. Bake for 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter (lightly).
Add soups, broth and chilies.
Add chicken and mix well.
Arrange in casserole: layer of tortillas, layer of chicken mixture, layer of cheese.
Repeat layering until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven or until brown.

title: manicotti with butternut squash filling
directions: Cook manicotti shells until al dent. Carefully rinse in cold water and reserve. Steam squash until tender. Mash thoroughly. Heat oil in a sautoir and saut onion and garlic until translucent. Add cabbage and sugar and continue to cook until cabbage is wilted. Add vegetable stock and squash and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add the Ricotta cheese and soy sauce and remove from heat. Mix well. Load mixture into piping bag and fill manicotti. Pour heated tomato sauce into baking dish and place filled manicotti on top. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven.
Yield: 4 portions.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and spread on cookie sheet.
Top that with chopped lettuce, onion, cheese and tomato. Eat with nacho chips.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt butter with milk, then add caramels and chocolate chips to melt. Add nuts. Bake 1/2 cake mixture 15 minutes. Pour other mixture on top of cake, then pour other half of cake mix. Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: mint brownies
directions: Cream and combine in order: sugar, 1/2 cup butter or margarine, eggs, Hershey's syrup, vanilla, salt and flour.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: kotlety pozharskie(ground chicken cutlets)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the 5 slices of bread and 1/4 cup of milk.
Soak the bread for about 15 minutes, then squeeze the bread dry with your fingers.

title: helen gray (pugs) cucumber pickles
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and salt; pour over pickles.
Store in refrigerator.

title: taco dip(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave.
Serve with chips.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter. Mix well. Press into bottom only of 13 x 9 in. baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool completely. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended. Fold in the Cool Whip. Spread over the crust and chill. Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on pkg. Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill completely. Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on pkg. Pour over chocolate pudding. Chill completely. Spread additional Cool Whip over top.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Pour through a funnel into hot grease (a Fry Daddy works well).
Cook on both sides until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Add toppings and eat while warm.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet brown ground beef;
add tomato sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
In
small
skillet
saute
onions
in butter until tender.
Stir in sour cream and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
In
11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, layer cooked fettucine.	Spoon sour cream mixture over noodles and top
with meat
mixture.
Sprinkle
with Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chiles rellenos(stuffed bell peppers)
directions: Cook ground beef and add spices if desired, then drain grease and put aside.

title: sandy's hearty beef cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large fry pan, brown beef, onion and green pepper. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In saucepan, mix ground beef mixture with all ingredients until cream cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Do not boil.
Serve in chafing dish or small crock-pot to keep warm.

title: exotic chicken salad(serves 10)
directions: Mix together lightly and add dressing mixture.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine, dissolve and add vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 3 tablespoons liquid.
Flake fish. Combine salmon and liquid, crumbs, celery, onion and egg.
Mix well.
Form into 5 patties.
Fry in lightly greased skillet.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, salt and evaporated milk to a boil and boil for 6 minutes (be sure to stir while cooking).
Add rest of ingredients. Take off stove and stir until well mixed and mixture starts to thicken.
Spread into a large cookie sheet.

title: crab munchies
directions: Beat egg with mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and seasoning. Add crab meat and bread crumbs.
Shape into crab tenders.
Broil about 6 inches from heat until golden brown.
Makes 15 Crab Munchies.

title: mint julep jelly
directions: Combine bourbon, water and sugar in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo.
Pour into glasses.
Add fresh mint sprig to each glass.
Seal.
Makes 4 to 5 (8-ounce) glasses.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine sliced peaches with sugar as desired. Mix next 3 ingredients together in a small bowl, then combine gently with peaches. Heat till just hot in a saucepan over medium heat. Pour into a 8 in round baking dish. Cut up butter and drop over the fruit. Add Biscuit Topper. Bake at 400° for 20 min or topper is done. Serves 6.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients, except paprika, and spread in dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Beat together until thickened.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Decorate with chocolate sprinkles or shavings of chocolate.
Chill.

title: julie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion and hamburger.
Cook on high until hamburger browns.
Take off burner.
Add Ragu sauce.
Fill both jars of Ragu 1/2 full of water and shake.
Pour into pot.
Cover sauce, water and hamburger with onion salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cook for 1 hour on medium heat, stirring often.
Cook noodles as directed on box while sauce is cooking.
Drain noodles before serving with sauce.

title: mixed fruit with honey sesame dressing
directions: Mix strawberries, pineapple cubes and kiwi fruit; toss with Honey Sesame Dressing. Chill.

title: hawaiian ribs(6 servings)
directions: Sprinkle ribs with garlic.
Brown 20 minutes in 450° oven.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix salt and water. Bring to a boil and add pecans. Boil for 1 minute, drain. Spread pecans on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until crisp.

title: lemon-mint ice tea
directions: In a 2-cup glass container, place the tea bags.
Fill with water and microwave for 3 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes, then add to 2-quart juice container along with the lemonade to make 2 quarts and chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Lightly mix in food processor or by hand.
Should be chunky. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with melba rounds or crackers.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco mix, tomato paste, salt and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Roll flour tortillas, stuffed with meat mixture and chopped olives.
Cover with cheese, followed by diced chilies, then remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy vegetable-stuffed peppers
directions: Cook halved peppers.
Combine kidney beans, broccoli and cheese.
Fill each pepper half with the mix.
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in skillet 15 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese baked chicken breasts
directions: Between waxed paper, crush crackers into coarse crumbs with rolling pin.
Mix well with salt, garlic salt and marjoram in a shallow bowl. Beat egg and water in another shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture and then coat well in the crumb mixture.
Place in moderately buttered shallow pan about an inch apart.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in preheated oven
at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Twelve chicken pulley bones can be substituted for breasts in which case baking time needs to be 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cream cheese sticks
directions: Cut butter and cream cheese into flour as for pie crust.
Add milk and knead dough for 2 minutes with electric beater or 4 minutes by hand.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Using 1/4 of the dough at a time, roll on a floured board to thickness of pie crust.
Brush on evaporated milk; sprinkle with sugar and nuts. With a pastry cutter or sharp knife, cut into strips, 2 inches long by 1 inch wide.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes; immediately remove sticks to cooling racks.

title: meat and noodle casserole
directions: Make medium white sauce by melting 4 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add cooked noodles, ham and peas.
Put into baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8. Beef or chicken is good too.

title: double bran gem muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.
In a bowl, combine wheat and oat brans, whole wheat flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a separate bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Pour onto dry mixture and mix until just combined. Scoop by 1/4 cupfuls into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until toothpick comes out sticky, but not wet.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add ground raisins.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal.
Make into balls and flatten a little.
Cookies stay moist and makes a big batch.

title: sweet "n" sour pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in shortening.
Spray a shallow 3-quart baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Remove chops to baking pan; season with salt and pepper.
Add carrots.

title: petite cherry cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix well.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake paper in muffin pan.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan with butter.
Beat eggs, one at a time in the butter and sugar.
Sprinkle Bundt pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Spread blueberries on batter.
Use remainder of batter over blueberries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with lettuce and spread with mayonnaise.
Put a thin layer of sliced onions on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and then frozen or cooked peas.
Add a layer of shredded Cheddar cheese and 1 layer of fried, crumbled bacon.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: spiced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over spices and tea and let steep for 15 minutes.
Remove tea and spices and add sugar and fruit juices. Serve hot.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Cream one cup of sugar with butter, then add flour, baking powder, salt and milk, mixing well. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Pour blackberries over batter. Sprinkle remaining sugar over berries. Pour boiling water over top, then bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serve plain or with cream.

title: weight watchers orange dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
After mixing well, fold in Cool Whip.
One half cup serving equals 1 fruit, 1/2 protein and 20 calories.

title: kid's blowing bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use wands or circled fingers to dip into mixture and blow bubbles.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet, then put them in shallow baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water. Sprinkle rice over chops.
Pour 2 cups water over rice.
Top with diced vegetables.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish brine
directions: Soak overnight.
Cover fish with brine.
Wash salt off, air dry and smoke.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham fat side down in shallow microwave baking dish. Cook on High for 21 minutes; turn ham over.
Drain pineapple slices, reserving juice.
Combine 2 teaspoons juice with brown sugar to make paste.
Spread over top of ham.
Place pineapple slices on top and stud with cloves.
Attach pineapple with toothpicks, if necessary.
Cook on High 8 minutes.
Let stand, covered with foil, about 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well with mayonnaise until it is creamy.

title: diabetic apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in a large bowl (except nuts). Pour into a lightly greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is good served warm with ice cream.
Makes 16 servings.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Mix tuna fish, cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and English peas in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add 3/4 cup crushed potato chips to mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 cup of crushed potato chips on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet cook the meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spoon in mounds of mashed potatoes over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas.
Add chocolate chips last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
They will be light in color.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Serve with crackers or chips of choice.

title: bread in a jar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into greased widemouth pint jars, filling 1/2 full.
Place jars on a baking sheet in the oven.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When bread is done, remove one jar at a time.
Wipe, sealing edge of jar with paper towel or cloth and screw cap on tightly.
The heat will vacuum seal the jar and the bread will keep for up to 1 year.
This recipe makes 8 pints.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli and seeds, bacon and onion.
Then mix sugar, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.

title: simple strawberry preserves
directions: Place strawberries in 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 2 minutes.
Stir in fruit pectin.
Cook on Full power for about 2 minutes or until a few bubbles surface.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well and add egg yolks.
Beat well again.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, starting and ending with flour.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites. Put in three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: fluffy jello
directions: Pour jello into large mixing bowl.
Pour in hot water.
Mix. Beat in sour cream.
Blend in favorite fruit or pie filling. Chill until molds.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs over top and then sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased pans.
Press 1/2 Pecan in center of each ball before baking.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5 to 8 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted water.
Drain and mix with soup, milk, shrimp, cheese and onion.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with chips and, if desired, paprika and more grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and pork in skillet; drain off grease.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, salt, pepper and garlic.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix corn and beans together.
Put in casserole.
Mix soup, cheese, onion, sour cream and salt.
Put on top of vegetables.
Add crackers to top.
Melt oleo; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Bake in pie shell for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and serve with crackers.

title: boston baked beans(in memory of winnie miller)
directions: Cook white beans until done.
In a casserole dish, combine beans, tomatoes and sugar.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter together, then add bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Place in glass 2-quart casserole dish and just before baking add raisins, vanilla and cinnamon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until set in 325° oven.

title: blond brownies(chew bread)
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
May add 1 cup coconut, 3 cups chocolate chips or 1 cup nuts.

title: key lime pie
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat egg whites until very stiff, adding sugar as you beat; set aside.
Beat yolks until light colored and fluffy.
Add lime juice and beat together.
Add the condensed milk and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in beaten egg whites until blended. Pour into pie shell and freeze.
Remove later and top with whipping cream.
Return to freezer.
Freeze again.
Let it sit out of freezer for 5 minutes before serving.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Mix vinegar, red wine, water, sugar, salt, pepper, sliced onion, mustard seed, cloves and bay leaves in a large deep bowl. Wipe meat with a damp cloth and place in bowl. Let stand in refrigerator for 2 days turning the meat.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted and blended. Pour into buttered pan.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in raisins and apples.
In a large bowl, combine egg, honey, oil and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix to form smooth batter.
Drop batter onto ungreased cookie sheets, using rounded teaspoonfuls.
Dip fingers in water and press dough down.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butterscotch bubble bread
directions: Butter angel food cake or Bundt pan.
Dump in frozen rolls. Blend pudding mix, brown sugar, spices and nuts in a bowl. Scatter over dough.
It will sift down between rolls as they thaw and rise.
Cut margarine in thin pats and arrange on top.
Cover with foil and go to bed, leaving covered pan to rise on counter at room temperature.
Next morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in center of oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from pan and turn onto a large plate.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Divide dough in half and roll into 2 rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 425° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans, then coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box, then pour cake mix batter over pecans and coconut.
Beat until smooth with mixer, the cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon in heaping tablespoonfuls, this mixture over top of cake mix, avoiding the sides of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cake will set as it cools.
It's ugly, but delicious!

title: chewy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until lightly foamy; add sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Mixture will be stiff.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine peaches, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Put into an 8-inch square baking dish. Combine flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, oatmeal, 1/2 teaspoon
cinnamon and margarine; mix until crumbly. Crumble over peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill and serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Slowly add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 1 pie.

title: pina colada
directions: In blender, combine pineapple juice, cream of coconut and vodka; blend until smooth.
(Can be made ahead.
Cover and refrigerate up to 4 hours.)
Before serving, puree in blender with ice.
Serve in tall glasses.
Garnish with flowers or fresh fruit. Makes 16 servings.

title: ann's chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions and set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Slowly add powdered sugar and milk, alternately.
Mix well.
Gently fold in two (8 ounce) cartons frozen whipped topping (thawed).
Spoon into pie shells.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and freeze until solid. Serve frozen.

title: orange nut ring
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in all but 1/4 cup of the pecans and raisins.
Add egg, shortening, orange peel, orange juice, vanilla and milk.
Mix just until blended.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Glaze while warm with mixture of:

title: favorite rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion until golden. Remove from heat; stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper; toss lightly to mix well.
In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, layer half the rice mixture, then half the chilies, then sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes, or until bubbly and hot.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Add other ingredients in casserole dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Put French fried onions on top of dish and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: bachelor's pie
directions: Combine onion, celery, beef and pepper in big skillet with a little cooking fat in it.
Brown slowly and stir constantly.
When browned, add the rest of the ingredients; stir until pretty hot again and pour into a greased baking dish.
Then on top, spread some mashed potatoes.
Bake at 390° until brown.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Use Bundt pan.

title: deer mcnuggets
directions: Cut deer into 2-inch strips.
Fill large bowl with milk.
Add all seasonings.
Add meat.
Refrigerate up to 6 hours, flour and fry.
(Every deer you see will be swimming in this marinade.)

title: squash raisin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, butter and squash in large bowl. In another bowl, mix sifted dry ingredients, then add wet ingredients and raisins.
Stir just until batter is moistened throughout.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups and bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: carrot cake cream cheese icing
directions: Melt butter in microwave 20 seconds.
Mix all ingredients together with mixer at high speed until well blended.

title: holiday spread
directions: Grind Spam and olives.
Mix with other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole(mark davis' favorite dish)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cool and drain broccoli.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Spray a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam or lightly grease dish.
Pour all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place fryer in saucepan; add Coca-Cola, catsup, salt and pepper.
Cook for about 45 minutes over medium heat.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on box.
Grease and flour a pan and bake at 350° until the edges turn loose.

title: apple relish
directions: Mix together; let boil for 15 minutes. Pack in jars and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: reduced fat broccoli quiche(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: spanish omelet
directions: Saute tomato, green pepper and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender; drain.
Combine eggs, water, salt and pepper; stir briskly with a fork until uniformly blended.
Stir in vegetable mixture, 2 tablespoons picante sauce and bacon.
Heat a 10-inch omelet pan or heavy skillet over a medium heat until hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and rotate pan to coat bottom.
Pour half of egg mixture into skillet. As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges of omelet with a spatula and tilt pan so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Fold omelet in half and place on a warm platter.
Repeat procedure with remaining 1 tablespoon butter and egg mixture.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Lay 4 chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package Lipton onion soup mix. Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
No peeking!

title: energy tonic
directions: Mix well and pour in juice jars.
Keep in refrigerator; drink 1/2 cup morning and night.

title: quick manicotti
directions: Cook shells; rinse in cold water.
Drain and set aside.
Saute beef and garlic; drain grease.
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayonnaise; stir well.
Stuff manicotti shells with meat mixture (a baby spoon works real well for stuffing shells).
Arrange shells in greased baking dish.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved beet liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add beets and heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, buttermilk and Crisco, then mix with dry ingredients.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Stores well in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks. This recipe makes a lot, 1/2 recipe may be plenty.

title: easy fudge brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir all ingredients except fudge topping and mint extract until just moistened.
Pour mixture into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass casserole dish which has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cook about 10 minutes and then spread fudge topping on top.
If you like a mint taste, stir in mint extract into the fudge topping before it is spread over the brownies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Blend together oil, vinegar, sugar, parsley flakes, seasoned salt, Italian seasoning and onion.
Cook noodles; drain.
Cut up cauliflower, green peppers, broccoli and carrots.
Mix all and refrigerate.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and cream until forms soft ball stage; add dates and cook until dates melt.
Add nuts; beat until stiff.
Pour mixture on wet towel and roll and cool in icebox, then cut in slices.

title: chili-cheese bars
directions: Grease pan.
Layer cheese and chilies. Blend eggs, flour and milk.
Pour over cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Sprinkle Old Bay on oysters.
Slice pimento into 12 slices, placing one on each oyster.
Wrap oyster in slice of bacon and skewer.
Broil about 8 minutes or until bacon is golden brown and crisp.

title: rhubarb crunch cobbler
directions: Mix brown sugar, oats, flour and margarine with cinnamon until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: blondies
directions: Melt sugar and margarine together.
Add flour, eggs, vanilla, and pecans.
Stir everything together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter extras
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, maple flavoring and peanut butter.
Blend in pudding, flour, baking soda and salt. Add chocolate chips.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Time: Approximately 1 hour.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together raw apples, brown sugar and water; let set about 10 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake at 350°.

title: marguerites
directions: Boil the sugar and water. Beat egg whites stiff and pour the frosting over them. Add the other ingredients. Pile the mixture on butter-thin crackers and brown in a very slow oven. Dainty and delicious.

title: gallon jug refrigerator bread
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm and stir in yeast.
Mix together flour, soda and sugar.
Add in the oil and the milk-yeast mixture.
Stir together thoroughly using a nonmetal spoon.
Put mixture in a wide mouth jar.
(Sun tea jar will do.) Put in refrigerator loosely covered.
After 3 1/2 hours, stir down; put lid on jug.
Dough is now ready to be used or can be kept in refrigerator up to 4 weeks. Bread can be made into rolls, loaves or cinnamon rolls.
After having enough flour worked in to be workable (no need for second rising), bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: new year's day dip
directions: Mix peas and tomatoes.
Serve with Tostitos as they have just the right amount of salt.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Put first 6 ingredients together and cool.
Add one cup sifted flour to yeast mixture and 3 eggs; beat together well.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups flour and make soft dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Make 3 balls.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll each ball in 12-inch circle like pie. Brush with butter.
Cut in 12 pieces like a pie.
Start from bottom and turn up to make crescent shape.
Put on greased sheet and brush with butter.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: best biscuits
directions: Put flour, baking powder and sugar into mixing bowl.
Stir with fork.
Slowly add 1 to 1 1/2 cups cream, stir constantly, just until dough comes together.
Place dough on floured board and knead for 1 minute.
Put dough flat to 3/4-inch to 1-inch thick. Cut with 2-inch round cookie cutter or drinking glass.
Brush both sides with melted butter.
Place buttered biscuits 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 18 minutes until browned.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Pour a large can of fruit cocktail in bowl; do not drain.
Add all other fruits you like, cutting them in small bite size pieces. Sprinkle the box of pudding over the fruit mixture and mix well.

title: e t's raspberry cordial
directions: Mix whiskey and raspberries together and let stand for 10 days in covered container.
Strain and throw away raspberries.
Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Cool.
Add to whiskey and then add lemon juice.
Strain again and bottle.
Doesn't need to be refrigerated.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients, then add fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 300° in glass dish.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pudding and milk, then beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Chill.
Grind cookies in food processor.
Layer cookies and cream mixture in a clean plastic flowerpot.
End with cookies.
Place an artificial flower in center of pot and serve with a clean garden shovel. Oreos will look like dirt.
Peanut butter cookies will look like sand. If using peanut butter cookies, then put in a clean plastic sandpail and use a sand shovel to serve with (plates can be small Frizbees).

title: fish florentine
directions: Cook spinach in water to cover until tender, 5 minutes at most.
Remove from heat and drain thoroughly.
Spread in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Spread fish fillets over spinach.
Combine mayonnaise with lemon juice and salt; stir to mix well.
Pour over fish and spinach to coat evenly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes until fish is done, not dry.
Serve hot with fresh lemon quarters.

title: poppy seed bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix together in large bowl all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: blushing apple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and put in bottom of pans. Sprinkle brown sugar over the butter.
Arrange apples on butter sugar coating.

title: cherry crisp squares
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oats and margarine together to make a crumb mixture.
Spread half of mixture in the bottom of an 8-inch pan. Spread cherry pie filling in pan; add remaining crumb mixture over top of cherry filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and milk into a 5-quart kettle.
Bring to boil and cook for 3 minutes, then take from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add oats and vanilla (do fast).
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: fried rice
directions: Chill rice in refrigerator.
In wok or large skillet, add 1 tablespoon of oil.
When heated to 200°, add egg and scramble. Remove egg and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons back to skillet or wok and cook onion and garlic until cooked about 1 minute.
Stir in shrimp and water chestnuts.
Cook until shrimp curl and turn pink, about 4 minutes.
Stir in cold rice and soy sauce until well mixed, then stir in egg.
Stir constantly until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; peel and dice.
Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese.
Put potatoes in a greased casserole.
Pour sauce over them and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until creamy.
Add Carnation milk, cream and vanilla; beat low. Pour into cold freezer can. Add 2% milk to full line on can. Freeze.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Combine bread, dry milk, baking powder, baking soda and apple pie
spice	in
blender.
Blend until bread is crumbled. Add applesauce,
eggs
and
bran.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in raisins. Spoon
batter into nonstick muffin cups sprayed with nonstick cooking
spray. Bake for 25 minutes in preheated 375° oven until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: sticky finger chicken wings
directions: Simmer chicken wings in enough soy sauce to cover bottom of electric skillet until half done.
Mix ginger and garlic with soy sauce after removing drummettes to cookie sheet.
Add brown sugar to soy sauce mixture and bring to a boil.
Pour over drummettes on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 60 wings.

title: pa. dutch cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage and carrots through shredder.
Mix remaining ingredients well and mix with shredded cabbage and carrots.

title: barbecued beef on a bun
directions: Combine all ingredients (except rolls) in a Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Shred by using fork.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, well drained.
Squeeze with hands to remove water.
Mix all ingredients 24 hours in advance.
Refrigerate.

title: oh boy waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a bowl.
Put eggs, milk and oil into a blender or mixer bowl.
Beat liquid ingredients until smooth, then add the sifted dry ingredients and combine well.
Bake on a hot waffle iron.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix well and pour in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chile con carne
directions: Mix meat with seasonings and put in pot after shortening has been heated.
Let it cook until done on a medium heat.
Add 1 cup of water, onion, chopped bell pepper and tomato sauce, also beans. Let this simmer for 10 minutes.
A serving for 6.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook for 10 minutes and serve on buns.

title: bavarian cole slaw
directions: Toss sliced/shredded vegetables in bowl.
In small saucepan, bring to boiling vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Pour hot dressing over vegetables.
Toss thoroughly. Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: date butterscotch chews
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and heat slowly, stirring constantly until blended.
Cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla; mix.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Stir into mixture in pan, blending thoroughly.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into small bars.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: apricot casserole
directions: In a 2 quart deep casserole dish that has been greased with butter, layer the above ingredients in the following order: apricots, brown sugar, crackers, and butter. Top layer should end with crackers and butter. When all the layering is done you should have 3 layers of apricots. Bake at 300 for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; remove from heat.
Mix ingredients except onions using only half of the cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake with lid on for 20 minutes at 350°.
Layer with the other half of cheese.
Top with 1/2 can Durkee fried onions.
tags: cream of chicken soup (Campbell's home-style cooking)

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Boil ribs for 10 minutes (no seasoning).
Put into large pan. Sprinkle with seasoning.
Slice bell peppers and onions over meat. Cover pan with foil; cook in oven for 45 minutes.
Pour off juice and baste with barbecue sauce.
Reheat under foil and enjoy.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts.
Remove meat from bones and cut in small pieces.
Mix chicken, soups and sour cream.
Spread chicken mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine and poppy seed.
Spread cracker mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english cucumber soup
directions: Wash but do not peel cucumbers.
Cut them into 1-inch chunks and puree along with remaining ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: 2-2-2 casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Season to taste.
Place half bag of crushed chips in bottom of pan.
Mix together meat, soup, tomatoes and olives.
Pour on top of crushed chips.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with remainder of crushed chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Use an electric mixer to cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and mix on low speed until thoroughly combined.
Stir in vanilla or lemon juice and zest.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 325 degrees. On a floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheets and refrigerate until firm, 15 minutes.
Bake for 8-10 minutes or until edges start to brown.
Cool on wire racks; decorate as desired.

title: lorna's russian tea
directions: Combine sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon in a saucepan. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.

title: cucumber stick pickles
directions: Mix lime in 2 gallons of water.
Pour over cucumbers and soak 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Slice onions and bell peppers.
Cover with ice water.
Let stand for 3 hours and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and pickling spice.
Pour over cucumbers; let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil for 20 minutes; put in jars and seal.

title: cincinnati-style chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring until tender.
Add beef or turkey and cook until browned.
Add chili powder, cinnamon, cumin, allspice, cloves, bay leaf, chocolate, broth, tomato sauce and vinegar.
Stir to mix well.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seashells and mushrooms and basil cream sauce
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
While pasta is cooking, heat a nonstick skillet over high heat.
Add mushrooms.
Sprinkle with basil, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender, stirring frequently.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of butter until crumbly.
Pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, noodles and 1/4 cup cheese; mix gently.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: s'more pie
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding mix.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie crust. Top with marshmallows.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: strawberry-angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, sugar and salt.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken; fold in Dream Whip.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cake pieces.
Pour mixture over cake.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours to set.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: double chocolate crinkle tarts
directions: Melt chocolate chips; cool to room temperature.
Sift together flour and salt.
Blend together shortening, margarine and 1/4 cup melted chocolate.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Divide dough into 12 baking cups in a muffin tin and press evenly around.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
I like to use more onion and garlic salt.

title: mushroom sauerkraut soup
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in cold water for 2 hours.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Add with the water, sauerkraut juice and onion; cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, brown flour in oil.
Stir constantly or the flour will scorch.
Add about a cup of the soup to the flour mixture and stir constantly to make zaprashka, add to the soup.
Cook slowly for another 2 to 4 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese toast bars
directions: Combine egg, mayonnaise, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, pepper and hot sauce in a bowl; mix well.
Stir in bacon. Trim crusts from bread; toast lightly on both sides.
Spread toast evenly with cheese mixture.
Cut each slice into 3 strips. Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Yield:
24 bars.

title: uncle dan's popcorn mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine popcorn, shoestring potato stix and nuts in large roasting pan.
Set aside.
Combine butter, dill, Worcestershire sauce, lemon pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, and red hot sauce in small bowl; pour over popcorn mixture, stirring until evenly coated.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stirring once.
Cool completely; store in air tight container.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat with hand mixer until smooth.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and cool slightly until thick, but not solid. Add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: salmon-asparagus divan
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid. Break into chunks.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Blend in flour.
Add half and half and reserved salmon liquid.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened.
Add seasonings, Parmesan cheese and salmon.
Heat gently.
Spoon over hot cooked asparagus. Garnish with toast triangles. Makes 6 servings.

title: indian succotash
directions: Combine ingredients, season and heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soft clay
directions: Mix flour, salt and alum together in a bowl.
Add oil and colored hot water.
Mix everything until it is cool enough for you to use.
If clay dries out, wrap in a damp cloth, put in a plastic bag and let stand for a couple of days.

title: irish potatoes glorious
directions: Peel, wash and cut potatoes in rings.
Put 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet.
Cover the skillet with rings of potatoes and lightly brown the rings on one side.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine with sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add flour, milk and flavoring all at once.
Beat batter until smooth.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Start in cold oven.

title: pear salad
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend thoroughly.
Pour into bowl.
Cover with miniature marshmallows and refrigerate until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken until tender, drain and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli until tender-crisp and place in buttered casserole dish.
Scatter chicken over the broccoli.
Mix the soup with mayonnaise and lemon juice and spread over chicken. Mix melted butter with the bread crumbs.
Spread grated cheese over soup mixture and top all with the buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook 45 minutes at 350° in covered dish.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water. Add the frozen strawberries; stir occasionally until thawed. Add the pineapple and bananas. Pour half into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill firm. Spread evenly with the sour cream. Pour remaining gelatin on top. Chill firm.

title: stromboli
directions: Make up dough.
Separate into 2 halves for crust and topping. Combine ingredients on top of crust, alternating, starting with pizza sauce.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until dough is done.

title: curried chicken
directions: In a large pan, saute apple, onion, garlic and curry powder in butter until tender. Gradually add flour, then cream and bouillon. Cook and stir until sauce boils for about 1 minute. Add seasonings and chicken; cook for 10 minutes. Serve on a bed of rice (about 3 to 4 cups).

title: nutritious french fries
directions: Clean and boil potatoes for 20 minutes.
Peel and shape into French fries.
Then place on cookie sheet slightly sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with sea salt.
Bake at 400° for approximately 50 minutes.
Turn after 25 minutes with a spatula.

title: grandmother's dressing
directions: Mix together and put in greased baking dish.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, then flour, sifted with salt.
Add shortening and beat smooth with eggbeater.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until easily pierced by fork.
Cool slightly.
Place cooked and peeled potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and evaporated milk. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet near center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack to insure a crispy pie shell when cooled.

title: rocks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, and soda and mix well.
Add salt and flour and mix.
Add nuts and raisins or dates.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: quick hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in large skillet
or heavy pot; pour off any fat. Add onion, tomato
juice,
mushrooms,
water and seasonings.
Cook until boiling;
cover
and	simmer	until at least half the liquid has
evaporated.
Add noodles and simmer until almost dry.	Stir in sour cream and heat a short time over low heat;	do not boil.

title: french meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vinegar and continue beating.
Slowly pour in sugar while beating.
Add the chocolate chips (mini chips are better).
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8 inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping on aluminum foil covered 14 inch pizza pan, press edges to seal.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, remove from foil onto serving plate.
Combine cream cheese, milk, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Glaze with combination of apricot preserves, water and strawberry extract.
Cut into wedges.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix together, put into greased muffin pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: seven layer cookies(from 1975 edition)
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread one layer of ingredients as listed.
Pour milk on top.
Pat mixture down.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes and cool before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate to cause firmness and serve with crackers.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Dice vegetables and saute in butter; add flour and stir thoroughly. Add clams. Gradually add water and let mixture come to a boil. Add potatoes and simmer for 15 minutes. Add tomatoes, catsup, spices and let simmer for additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: missionettes taco soup
directions: Brown and simmer ground beef or chicken with the taco seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until you are ready to serve.
(This can be done in a crock-pot.)

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix together.
Mix ingredients together.
Store in large jar or Tupperware, sealed airtight.
Refrigerate.
Keeps 10 days.
Serve on lettuce leaf or with cooked pasta as a salad.

title: chicken quiche amandine
directions: Place chicken and almonds in pie shell, then Swiss cheese. Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl. Blend in milk, salt, mace and pepper. Pour over cheese. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese. Bake in a preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: tomatoes with corn pudding
directions: Core tomatoes. Scoop out seeds and pulp. Sprinkle shells with salt and pepper. Invert on paper towels and drain 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge or frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, together thoroughly. Stir over low heat until chocolate and margarine are melted. Then, stirring constantly, bring rapidly to a full boil.
Boil to 220° or until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.

title: crispy coconut balls
directions: Melt butter, add marshmallows.
Stir in cereal.
Roll in coconut.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Spread apple filling in buttered 9-inch square baking pan. In bowl, beat eggs.
Add condensed milk, melted margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over apples.
In a bowl, combine sugar and flour; cut in cold margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts and oats.
Sprinkle over custard.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: juicy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Mix cereal, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in cereal, salt and pepper mixture until well coated.
Place chicken skin side up in pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake until chicken is done, about 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Roll out and cut.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour, then bake for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix and vanilla; mix well. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Set aside.
Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Gradually mix in the rest of the ingredients, adding apples last.
Can sprinkle additional cinnamon on top.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Best when served warm with milk.
No icing needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare instant rice before mixing.
Add other ingredients to rice.
Mix well and place in ungreased baking dish.
May add more cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar, tapioca and salt together in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Stir in vanilla; cool.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Saute onions and pepper with butter for 5 minutes.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add corn, sugar, salt and tomatoes; simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in blended flour and water; cook for 15 minutes. Serve with salad, corn muffins and mixed fruit.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer on top of stove for 20 minutes.

title: microwave pecan or peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, syrup, butter in a microwave safe 2-quart bowl. (I've found 2-quart Pyrex measuring cup great.)
DO NOT STIR!! Place in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Take out and stir in paraffin wax square.
Then stir in
desired nuts.
Cook on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Pour into pans sprayed with Pam.
(If microwave is slow, you may have to cook a little longer.)

title: rigatoni pasta salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and spices together.
Cook, rinse and cool pasta.
Mix all together.
Put cucumber and onion slices on top. Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread and sausage stuffing
directions: In a large skillet melt butter.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in poultry seasoning, thyme and garlic powder.
Combine corn bread, vegetable mixture and sausage. Add broth; toss gently.
Spoon into 13x9-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with turkey gravy, if desired.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Add soup, water, seasonings, corn and green pepper.
Mix and simmer 15 minutes. Fill greased baking dish 3/4 full with mixture, leaving room for corn bread topping.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix together thoroughly margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix powdered sugar, nuts and cinnamon together and set aside.
Pour half batter into lightly greased Bundt pan and sprinkle with half nut mixture.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle nuts on top. Increase oven temperature to 350 degrees.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Invert onto dish.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: chicken in phyllo dough
directions: Flatten the chicken breast halves between sheets of plastic wrap until they are 1/4-inch thick.
In a bowl, combine the cheeses, pepper, parsley, tarragon and 8 tablespoons butter, cut into bits.
Form the mixture into eight 3-inch oval patties. Arrange 1 patty on each of the chicken breasts and roll up, tucking in the sides, to enclose the filling completely.
Brush 1 sheet of the phyllo with some of the remaining butter, melted and cooled, and top it with another sheet.
Brush the sheet with the butter and arrange 1 of the chicken rolls in the center of a short side.
Roll the phyllo, tucking in the sides to enclose the chicken completely; put the package in a baking dish and brush it with butter.

Make other packages with the remaining phyllo, butter and chicken rolls in the same manner and bake the packages in a preheated 350° oven, basting them with the pan juices occasionally, for 40 minutes, or until they are golden.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well. Store in airtight container. Add 4 or 5 spoonfuls to each cup of boiling water. Top with mini marshmallows.

title: almond delights
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Crust:
Mix well the flour, butter and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, nutmeg and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate covered nougats
directions: Mix condensed milk, 4x sugar, butter, vanilla and nuts; chill thoroughly.
Roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin in a double boiler first.
Add chocolate and melt.
Beat until smooth.
Dip balls into mixture until coated on all sides.
Drop on wax paper.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix together milk and flour; cook over very low heat until thickened.
Let cool.
Take butter and sugar and cream until fluffy, then add the cooled milk and flour mixture and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla (can use lemon juice and yellow food coloring for a change); blend again.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broccoli and rice to a boil.
Saute margarine and onion. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Layer in baking dish in order given.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Top each chicken breast with cheese slice.

title: travie's special
directions: Melt some carob chips.
Put a little peanut butter on animal crackers.
Dip in melted carob and enjoy.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all ingredients, except ham and cheese, in blender. Blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese over top.
Press gently below surface with back of spoon. The pie pan will be extremely full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set ten minutes before cutting.

title: sis' pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well with a pastry cutter. Add ice water; mix thoroughly to make dough.
Divide dough in half.
Roll on floured surface to desired size.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Bring vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper to a boil. Remove from heat and cool. Beat eggs and fold into mixture. Cook until thick, like pudding. While still hot, stir in salad dressing. Can use with hot or cold potatoes.

title: orange candy
directions: Put 1 cup of sugar into a heavy frying pan and stir with a wooden spoon over medium heat until the sugar is melted and caramelized to a golden brown color.
Add the water and stir until the sugar completely redissolves.
Add the remaining 2 cups sugar, evaporated milk, and salt.
Place over low heat and stir until the mixture begins to boil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until it reaches the soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm, without stirring.
Add the orange peel and nuts.
Beat until the candy loses its gloss and will holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Pour into a lightly buttered 8-inch square pan and cool until set.
Cut into squares before candy becomes too firm.

title: cherry salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Stir constantly, then cool.
Add mixture to drained cherries and sliced bananas.

title: nutty apricot snack loaf
directions: Soak apricots in warm water for 15 minutes.
Drain, cut in pieces.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together. Cream shortening; add gradually sugar, creaming well.
Blend in egg.
Beat well and add water that the apricots were soaked in and orange juice.
Mix well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts and apricots.

title: cheese buttons
directions: Allow margarine to soften at room temperature. Combine with other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Roll into balls the size of a small marble. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork. Will be about the size of a quarter. Bake at 325° until light tan, about 18 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Mix first six ingredients into fine crumbs. Press half of mixture into a 9x13 greased pan. Boil dates, sugar and water until soft. Cool. Pour over top of crumb crust. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine chocolate and milk in double boiler.
Heat over hot water until chocolate melts; stir to blend.
Remove from stove and add powdered sugar and nuts.
Cool slightly.
Form into balls; roll in coconut.
Makes 25 balls.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with pie filling just before eating.

title: peaches 'n' cream
directions: Mix Bisquick, egg, margarine and milk.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Place peaches on top of batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice; beat for 2 minutes and spoon on top of peaches (not to edge).
Mix and sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl.
Place beaten eggs into a cup and fill cup with cream or canned milk. Make a well in flour and pour in egg mixture.
Mix with fork until dough forms a ball and sticks to the fork.
Divide dough into 2 parts and enough flour to roll out.
Cut into desired size and drop into boiling water.
Stir often and cook uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: marvalyn's bread pudding
directions: Soak bread with
milk, combine all ingredients and mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake yellow cake.
Let cool.
Cut in small squares. Place in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer with strawberry glaze, fresh strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Repeat until punch bowl is full.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg; mix until smooth.
Stir in molasses and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place two inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Cream butter and flour.
Add milk; make a thick cream sauce. Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup, bay leaf, red pepper and lemon juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked shrimp; allow to get very hot.
Serve in a ring of ice.
Serves 6.

title: mimi's easy six-layer bars(makes 48 pieces)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine by warming oven and watching.
Remove when melted and sprinkle with graham crackers, then, in order, layer coconut and chips.
Drizzle condensed milk throughout.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove and cut when slightly warm into 48 squares.
Also great with butterscotch chips and slivered almonds.

title: butter bran bread
directions: Mix together and let cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve 2 packages yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add 2 or 3 cups whole wheat flour; mix well.
Add 1/2 of 5 or 6 cups white flour.
Mix well and add rest of flour.
Makes 2 (2 pound) loaves.

title: zucchini casserole(new to us)
directions: Cook whole squash 5 minutes in salted water.
Cool and slice thin; sprinkle with salt (if you like).
Mix yolks, sour cream and flour; fold into whites, then mix with squash.
In a 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish layer 1/2 the squash mix with 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the bacon.
Repeat and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and pour juice into a saucepan.
Mix pineapple with marshmallows and set aside.
In saucepan, add juice, flour, sugar, egg and vinegar.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Mix well with Cool Whip and juice mixture.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Add diced apples and peanuts.
Taste best if made ahead of time.

title: thanksgiving applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt and stir into shortening mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and cut up candy. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add meat (cut in thin strips or small pieces), garlic, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir-fry until meat is tender and hot, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add peas and carrots. Stir well into rice-meat mixture.
Push rice-meat mixture to sides of skillet or wok; add beaten eggs and cook briefly before stirring through rice-meat mixture.
Continue to stir until eggs are completely cooked.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: swiss mocha
directions: Combine; sift and store in airtight container.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Add cabbage and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add pepper and stir 5 more minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and continue cooking 5 minutes longer.
Add sugar, vinegar and seed and continue cooking and stirring 2 to 3 additional minutes until heated.
Nice to serve with pork or corned beef.

title: potato basque soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage over medium heat.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices; spread each with cheese.
Cook asparagus until just tender.
Chill.
Lay one piece asparagus diagonally across slice of bread.
Turn opposite corners over asparagus, overlapping.
Press firmly to seal.
Wrap several sandwiches together in waxed paper.
Place in covered container and chill for several hours.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Add beaten egg yolks to hot water and beat until foamy.
Add superfine sugar until dissolved.
Then add lemon juice and zest. Dissolve plain gelatin in cold water, then heat to dissolve completely.
Add the gelatin mixture to the egg yolk mixture, blending gently.
Place in the refrigerator and let set (not fully).
Add the whipped egg whites and whipped cream by folding into the lemon/gelatin mixture that is not yet fully set.
Let set fully and then serve, garnished with whipped cream.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients together and empty in pie shell.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: manwich pizza
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix with Manwich sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place biscuits and press together until bottom is covered.
(This may take a few minutes.)
Cover with ground beef mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak.
Brown in hot oil.
Add tomatoes, onion and celery. Cover and cook over low heat or in a moderate oven at 300° until tender (2 to 2 1/2 hours), uncovering the last 1/2 hour to cook down sauce to a rich thickness.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Stir flour, sugar and baking soda together.
Cut in shortening until size of peas. Mix buttermilk with yeast-water.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
May now be covered and refrigerated overnight to be shaped and baked later.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour and margarine or butter until it's crumbly.
Add nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden (about 12 minutes).
Let cool, then add layers one at a time.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix grape jam and chili sauce in large heavy pan.
Roll meat into
very
small
meatballs.
Cook
in sauce for 1 hour. Serve hot over rice or serve with toothpicks for party.

title: setting sun summer cooler
directions: Spoon grenadine evenly into 2 glasses.
Combine juice and soda; pour gently into glass.
Serves 2.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough firmly into the bottom of a pizza pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 13 minutes (or until brown).

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Boil cabbage for 5 minutes in water.
Drain well.
Combine butter, salt and flour in saucepan.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until bubbly.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese to white sauce and pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and butter over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut butter lengthwise into 4 sections.
Place one piece of butter at narrow end of chicken breast.
Sprinkle with parsley and onion salt.
Roll up in jelly-roll fashion, starting at butter end.
Dip in beaten egg. Then dip in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate 1/2 to 1 hour.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken in a basket
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil and butter and garlic when browned. Add rosemary, salt and pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on low.
Remove chicken and saute mushrooms.
Deglaze pan with sherry and add green olives (as many as you like).
Add chopped parsley.
Hollow out round bread and slightly toast in oven with butter and garlic.
Put chicken with mushrooms and olives in bread.
Pour sauce over this. Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° and serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine
ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with assorted
raw vegetables.
