directions: Boil the shrimp in Tony's seasoning until they are cooked. Drain them and mix the shrimp, chopped vegetables, lettuce, sauce, mayonnaise, olive oil and Tony's well.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with Captain's wafers.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat over medium heat; bring to boil, then simmer 15 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Beat 1 egg white until stiff, fold into other ingredients. Dip fish and deep-fry.

title: sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Brown in heavy skillet 1 pound sausage.
Leave some bits to stick to bottom of skillet and brown.
This gives good flavor and color to gravy.
Remove browned sausage to plate.
Leave about 1/4 cup of drippings in skillet.
(If too lean, add margarine to make 1/4 cup.)

title: taylor's barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half; skin legs and 8 thighs (optional). Bring to boil in 4-quart pan for 15 to 25 minutes.
Remove and place in shallow pan.
Cover with sauce.
Grill or broil until brown.

title: creamed beets
directions: Combine vinegar, butter, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon water in saucepan.
Bring to boiling point.
Stir in sour cream and beets. Cook over low heat until beets are heated through.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg lightly, add water, then salmon, bread crumbs, onion, salt, melted butter.
Mix well.
Mold into a loaf.
Bake in a greased pan at 325°.
Serve plain or with tomato sauce.

title: trish's polska kielbasa soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, water, Polska kielbasa and carrots. Simmer for one hour, then add cabbage and broccoli.
Simmer until tender, then add instant potatoes to desired thickness.
Pepper to taste.
Knorr all-purpose seasoning to taste.

title: ice cream peach pie
directions: Make Jell-O; mix 1 cup of ice cream until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and fold in peaches.
Pour into pie shell.
Keep in fridge 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Substitute with your favorite flavor.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken breast, break into pieces.
Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on pkg.
Combine above with soup and mayonnaise.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Cream egg yolks with sugar.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and dry ingredients, alternating.
Add salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in batter.

title: three cheese spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cool in a bowl of cold water; set aside.
Saute onion and red pepper with 3 tablespoons of butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine spinach, onion, red pepper, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella, Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan and egg; set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Put orange sections in bowl.
Mix with cinnamon and honey. Add coconut.
Let flavors blend at room temperature for 10 to 30 minutes.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Chop parsley and garlic together.
Heat oil; add chopped parsley and garlic.
Saute 10 seconds.
Add clams and liquid.
Add pepper to taste.
Heat through, about 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked linguini.

title: potato ring
directions: Cook potatoes and mash; add remaining ingredients.
Put in ring mold; sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° until brown or make potato pancakes and fry in skillet.
Serves 8.

title: baked stuffed red fish
directions: Melt shortening in frying pan.
Add bread crumbs.
Stir until crumbs are golden brown, then add seasonings and salt.

title: healthful oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix together all dry ingredients (don't sift).
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins, pecans and carrots.

title: firecrackers
directions: Place
about
1/4 cup of potato salad in center of each slice of boiled ham.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.
Stick a	small sprig of parsley in one end of each roll for a fuse. Kinda purty and real easy.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in 3 tablespoons of oil until onions are yellow.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain off grease and add salt, pepper, chili powder, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus, shrimp and shells bake
directions: Cook pasta to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain. Meanwhile, heat oven to 350°. Spray 2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic; cook about 1 minute. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended; cook until bubbly. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low. Stir in 1 cup of the cheese. Cook, stirring constantly until smooth. Remove from heat. Add cooked pasta, shrimp, asparagus and parsley; toss gently to mix. Pour into sprayed casserole. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese. Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until casserole is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Place all ingredients except ginger ale in a 1-gallon container. Add enough water to make 1 gallon. Freeze several hours before serving; remove punch from freezer. Allow it to get to a slushy stage.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: skillet apples
directions: Over medium heat, in a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Then add sugar and cornstarch, mix well.
Add water, cinnamon and apples; cover for 12 to 15 minutes until tender.
Spoon sauce over apples occasionally.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in a pan.
Add milk and butter. Bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and stir. Cool for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Put on cake.

title: lime punch
directions: Follow	directions
on	package to dissolve jello, then add sugar.
Stir
well.
Add
can of frozen lemonade, then add pineapple juice, water and food coloring.
Refrigerate.

title: foiled trout
directions: Chop the vegetables fine and saute them in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Split and clean the trout; stuff each with the vegetables.
Dot with butter and place 3 inches from the broiler.
Broil 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Place fish in foil.
Crimp edges of foil to seal.
Oil the foil. Place on buttered cookie sheets and bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: corn casserole #2
directions: Mix Bisquick, corn, egg, oil and milk.
Pour half mixture into a greased pan.
Sprinkle chilies and cheese on this.
Pour the rest of the mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy ham quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Let cool on a rack.
Place ham in pastry shell.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in half and half and seasonings.
Pour over cheese in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Yields 1 (9-inch) quiche.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in pan.
Cover with 1 bag stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
May add vegetables if desired.

title: pecan pork loin roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Melt oleo and put apples or raspberries (or fruit of choice) into melted oleo mixture; then pour first mixture over it in a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curried limas and chicken wings
directions: Pick over beans and rinse under running water.
Combine beans and water in a large kettle; cover and soak overnight.
Bring soaked beans to a boil over low heat.
Partially cover and simmer 35 minutes or until beans are almost tender.
Cut each wing at joint to separate the 2 large sections.
Melt butter in a large skillet; add the wings and cook slowly until brown.
Remove wings to paper toweling to drain when brown.
Add onion, carrots, curry powder and cinnamon to fat remaining in skillet.
Saute until onion is tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Reserve 2 cups; if needed, add enough water to have 2 cups of liquid.
Add remaining liquid to flour mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling.
Add milk and peas; bring to a boil.
Combine beans, chicken wings and curry sauce in a 3 to 4-quart baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until beans are tender, stirring halfway through baking.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Combine coconut, raisins and pecans; place in uncooked pie shell.
In a bowl, whisk together margarine, salt, vanilla, sugar, eggs, milk and flour.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until top is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potpourri
directions: Simmer on the back burner during the day and evening.
It gives a lovely fragrance throughout the house.

title: treasure cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs, peanut butter and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from baking sheet at once.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice on bottom of 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Set aside. Brown pork chops.
Put pork chops on top of rice.
Put a thick slice of tomato, green pepper and onion on each chop.
Sprinkle with spices and pour beef consomme on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pops
directions: You will need 4 wooden sticks.

title: all time favorite grape-nuts pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add scalded milk gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into six custard cups or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Grape-Nuts.
Dot with butter.
Place custard cups or casserole in pan of hot water. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves six.

title: sour cream and cranberry pork
directions: Slice the pork into about 2-inch thick slices.
Make an indentation in each slice.
Combine parsley and garlic and pack into the indentations.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a medium frying pan and saute the pork slices in the hot butter, first on the unstuffed side, and then turning onto the stuffed side.
When lightly browned, remove from the pan and set aside. Melt remaining butter in the same pan.
Add the flour and milk to make a smooth sauce.
Return the meat to the pan; cover and simmer 20 minutes, turning once.
Add sour cream and the cranberry sauce and heat through.
Serve over a platter of noodles.
Serves 4.

title: shoe maker's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan over a medium flame, heat the apples without water until very tender, stir occasionally. Watch closely or will burn.
Mash the apples and sugar to taste. Add raisins, melted butter and then the yolks.
Gently fold in egg whites and mix well.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs to make an even coating.
Pour half the apple mixture in the pan and sprinkle the top with the other 1/2 cup of bread crumbs.
Then add remainder of apple mixture and top with the other 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake for about 50 minutes until the cake is firm and light brown.
Remove, cool and remove ring.
Serve cut into wedges with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil the zucchini.
Cut each zucchini in half lengthwise. Scoop out seeds and discard.
Scoop out zucchini meat and dice. Mix zucchini with bread crumbs, shredded cheese, onion and eggs. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stuff zucchini shells with this mixture.
Top with shredded cheese or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until golden brown on top.

title: granny's fruit salad
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar and sugar in double boiler on low heat stirring all the time.
When thick take off heat and add 2 Tbsp. butter.
Cool mixture.
Add whipped whipping cream.
In another bowl, add pineapple, fruit cocktail, marshmallows, cherries and nuts.
Mix with cream mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.
Freezes well, too.

title: candied yams
directions: Cut up sweet potatoes and place in a lightly greased shallow baking dish. In a small pan, melt butter. Stir in cornstarch, salt and cinnamon. Cook and stir for a minute or 2; pour evenly over potatoes. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Place tea, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bag and steep in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Stir in the cherry gelatin and let mixture cool.
Add the orange juice, lemon juice, cranberry juice and the sugar.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Serve warm, keep any extra in the refrigerator.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Barely cook broccoli; place in buttered casserole dish.
Add a layer of chicken pieces.
Cover with sauce (soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder).
Put sauce over chicken.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumbs, mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in microwave.
Mix with Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken gismonda
directions: Pound out chicken breasts.
Dip in beaten eggs and seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until done.
Clean and slice mushrooms. In a separate pan, saute mushrooms in butter.
Cook spinach according to directions on box.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat au jus, wine and cornstarch.
Add mushrooms to au jus.

title: ambrosia
directions: Cook, drain and cool pepe in refrigerator.
Drain fruit and save all fruit juices.
In saucepan cook eggs, flour, sugar and juices until thickened.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix all fruit, pepe and marshmallows with thickened pudding like.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Delicious . . . Delicious.

title: rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Whip egg whites and fold in.
Mix in vanilla.
Remove 1/4 cup flour and put aside.
Sift flour with cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts and raisins to separate them.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Add soda in water and mix. Add floured nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful about size of unshelled walnut on cookie sheet.
Do not smooth down. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Keep in covered can.
Makes 12-14 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and spicy curry dip
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, heat the chutney and curry powder for 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Cool slightly.
In a small bowl, combine curry mixture and pepper sauce.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves(greece)
directions: Brown meat and onions until meat is crumbly and onion golden in color.
Add rice and rest of ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.
In separate container, boil cabbage until slightly tender.
Separate leaves and cool.
(If cabbage leaves are too large, cut in half.) Place one heaping tablespoonful of filling on each leaf and roll in ball shape.
Arrange a few of the outer leaves in medium kettle. Arrange cabbage rolls close together in kettle, over leaves.
Add chicken broth or water to cover.
Place a heavy plate over rolls so they will not break during cooking.
Cover kettle and cook for 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Pour off all liquid reserving it to make Egg-Lemon Sauce (Avogolemeno Sauce).

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Layer uncooked chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place frozen broccoli on top.
Add undiluted soup mix.
Place on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Crumb crackers and sprinkle all over pan.
Melt butter and pour over entire pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese-rice fondue(more like a souffle)
directions: Heat rice, Cheddar cheese and milk until cheese melts.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Add beaten egg yolks and then the beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ground beef and chili powder in large skillet; cook over medium heat until browned.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: hot chili(for cold days)
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve with crackers and cheese.
Grate cheese on chili.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; let cool.
Add juice and fruit.
Pour into trays; let freeze.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.
Scoop into glass and pour 7-Up over top.

title: french toast(baked)
directions: Line the bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
With 1/2 of the bread cubes layer; put the cream cheese on top.
Beat the eggs, syrup, milk and oleo and rest of bread.
Pour over bread cubes.
Let set. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: mock chicken loaf
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Then add garlic powder and savorex, stirring until softened and mixed.
In a large mixing bowl combine bread crumbs, cream, eggs, cottage cheese, oats and gravy mix.
After blending, add the sauteed onions and celery.
Bake in 2 large loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until nicely browned.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Place biscuits into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ground beef, pizza sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick midget meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into loaf and place in microwavable pan.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at Medium power for 14 to 16 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Pour milk into double boiler.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and flour.
Pour into milk and cook until thick.
Cool custard.
Beat egg whites and vanilla.
Add to custard.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Beat eggs and add brown sugar and milk.
Add salt, vanilla, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir altogether.
Stir in the oatmeal.
Put in a large lightly buttered baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: punch for all
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add sugar and water.
Stir all together.
Can be stored in refrigerator.
Before serving, add ginger ale.
May also use as needed.
Add 1/4 cup ginger ale to 1 cup punch.
Refreshing!

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
If dough is too stiff, add a very small amount of milk.
The dough should look dry, but hold together when rolled in hands.
Roll in small balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Be careful when you take from cookie sheet for they tend to break until cool.
Makes large batch. This is an old, old recipe.
In fact, I used to store them in a lard can or in a dishpan covered with a cloth.
Very good.

title: never-fail corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add mixed together flour and sugar. Add milk and beat.
Add corn and melted butter.
Pour into well-buttered casserole.
Cook in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: gapirotada(bread pudding)
directions: In the medium saucepan, bring the water, brown sugar and cinnamon to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 3 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Cut toast in 1-inch pieces. Fold into the sugar mixture along with raisins and nuts.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar until well blended.
Cut cake in half to make 2 layers.
Spread cream cheese mixture between layers; pour glaze and strawberries over top. Serve immediately.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together all other ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
(Do not drain broccoli.)
Pour batter over butter.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Can prepare ahead and refrigerate until ready to bake.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and milk at medium speed.
Add hot potatoes gradually, beating constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pheasant steak
directions: Use only the breast of pheasant.
Cut into steaks.
Roll steaks in flour mixture.
Cook in 1/4 cup butter which has been melted in a skillet.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, turning once.
Prepare at least 1 pheasant per hungry rancher!
The other parts can be used in casseroles.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients; add well beaten egg and melted shortening and enough milk to make fairly moist stiff batter.
Drop by spoonful into boiling liquid.
Cover very closely; cook 18 minutes.
Delicious!

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat first four ingredients together until well blended. Gently fold in fluffy clean snow until the liquid is mushy thick. Eat immediately.
Serves 4.

title: salsa (hot)
directions: Combine and simmer about 20 minutes.
Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, soften cream cheese on Medium (50%) for 2 minutes.
Blend in 1/3 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon flavoring and egg. Pour into cooked pie crust.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) 6 minutes, rotating once, if necessary.

title: chewy chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add water, vanilla and egg yolks (reserve egg whites in separate bowl) and beat 2 minutes.
Beat in flour, salt, baking soda and powder. Spread batter in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks, then add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Spread over chips and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: christmas morning "wife saver"
directions: In a buttered 9 x 13-inch glass dish, place 8 slices of bread. Cover with bacon, then cheese and top with bread to resemble a sandwich.
Beat eggs in bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, melt butter (or margarine) and pour over top.
Add crushed corn flakes.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: spice cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan or kettle.
Heat just to boiling and then simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
You can also use a large coffee pot placing spices in basket.
Perk and serve.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies (food processor works well) spread 1/2 of crumbs over 9 X 13 pan. Let ice cream and cool whip soften in large bowl, add vanilla and mix well. Spread over crumbs and sprinkle with the rest of crumbs. Keep in freezer. Keeps well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add zucchini to the mixture.
Sift flour and add soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add crushed pineapple, raisins and nuts. Place into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine fruit, flour, sugar, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and orange juice.
Put into greased cake pan.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a medium bowl combine first four ingredients.
Add apples and celery.
Toss to mix well. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 5 cups.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut in a greased 9X12 inch pan. Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour over pecans and coconut. In a separate bowl, melt cream cheese and butter together. Add powdered sugar to this mixture. Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: stir fry veggies #3
directions: Heat broth in a wok. Saute onion, garlic and ginger root until onion is transparent. Add carrots, celery and broccoli. Mix well. Add 3 tablespoons water, cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes over high heat. Add water chestnuts and scallions. Cook 1 minute more, then add bean sprouts and soy sauce. Stir until well mixed and sprouts are heated through. Vegetables should be tender, yet crisp. Must serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
In large bowl combine spaghetti, dressing, vinegar, onion, pepper, pimentos and salad seasoning.
Mix thoroughly and chill well before serving.

title: favorite chicken breast
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate breasts in 1/2 juice mixture for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce with a dollop of mayonnaise.
Yields 12 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon pie filling evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator so that flavors will blend. Delicious served with fresh vegetables, cut up.
Also, good served with ???.

title: magically moist chicken
directions: Brush chicken on all sides with Hellmann's real mayonnaise. Place bread crumbs in large plastic food bag.
Add chicken one piece at a time; shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake in 425° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Makes four servings.

title: pie-cake mix dessert
directions: Pour pie filling into an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: lo-cal blueberry jam
directions: In a saucepan, mash blueberries.
Stir in pectin and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in sweetener.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Spoon into jars.
Cool; cover, seal and refrigerate.
Yield:
1 1/2 pints.

title: raisin-nut bread
directions: Mix walnuts, raisins, baking soda and salt with a fork.
Add shortening and water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°. Add to this mixture the eggs, vanilla, sugar and flour, mixing only to blend.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: betsy goodie bar
directions: In top of double boiler over simmering water melt chocolate with butter.
Remove from heat.
Beat in dry milk powder, peanut butter and vanilla with wire whisk or beater until fairly smooth. Stir in peanuts and raisins.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 48 2-inch bars.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 teaspoons of mix for 1 cup of tea.

title: barbecued chicken(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients for sauce in saucepan.

Heat thoroughly. Parboil chicken. Dip chicken in sauce and cook on grill until done. This sauce is delicious, so serve the sauce in a small bowl on each plate for dipping the chicken while eating. Be sure to have potatoes and bread with this so you can dip that too.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Place into 1 1/2-quart baking dish the bread cubes.
Blend together other ingredients and pour over bread.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water (1 inch deep).
Bake until done, about 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Line bottom of oblong glass baking dish with 1/2 the cookies. Mix ice cream and Cool Whip with mixer; pour 1/2 over cookies in dish.
Add remaining cookies, then cover with remaining ice cream and Cool Whip mixture.
Cover and let freeze overnight.
Set out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: *bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and baking soda overnight.
Drain. Place beans in pot with water. Add paprika, onions, carrots and celery. Bring to a boil.
Add 1/4 cup oil.
Let it boil for 5 minutes.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until tender. Add tomato sauce and stir.
When beans are tender (not mushy), add salt, pepper and parsley. Tastes better the second day.

title: oven fried chicken with biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) in oven.
Mix baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken and place, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes. Insert clove in each peach half.

title: stuff
directions: Brown meat.
Drain grease.
Add corn, beans and seasoning mix.
Cook until good and hot in greased casserole with cornbread mixture on top.
Sprinkle cheese
on top.
Mix cornbread according to box directions.
Bake until bread is done or lightly brown. Bell peppers and onion are optional.

title: pancit
directions: Cook garlic in oil until barely brown.
Add celery and carrots and stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add zucchini, onion and pork. Stir-fry about 1 minute.
Use 1 packet from noodles to flavor. Cook noodles according to directions on pack, but use only 1 flavor packet.
Drain noodles and toss together with stir-fried vegetables.
Season with soy sauce to taste.

title: busy day dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer gently covered for 30 minutes.
Add more water if a thinner stew is desired.

title: aunt catherine's cracker pudding
directions: Cook all together; beat whites of eggs for top.
Brown in oven.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Spoon dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until slightly brown.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat, then add peanut butter, oats, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir together very well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand 1 hour.
Makes 4 dozen.
More like candy than a cookie.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Press the rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
After cooling, spread mixture on top.
Top with broccoli, cheese or whatever you would like for a topping (vegetables, finely chopped, are great)!

title: lemon rice
directions: Melt margarine/butter in saucepan.
Add rice; cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring until rice grains become opaque and glisten. Add water, bouillon cube, lemon peel and salt; stir until cube is dissolved.
Cover.
Cook over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Remove lemon peel.
Stir.
Continue to cook until liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes, until rice is tender.
Combine eggs and grated cheese.
Stir into hot rice.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy chicken and rice bake
directions: Grease bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread wild rice over bottom of dish.
Sprinkle rice seasoning evenly over top of rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
In saucepan heat soup and water until boiling.
Pour soup evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash on top to taste.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake another 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain. Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken on top. Combine next 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes until heated.

title: healthy breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread evenly in 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Layer ham, red pepper and cheese over bread and set aside.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for melted butter and mix well.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
After bread is done, pour melted butter over top evenly and allow to soak.

title: pickle-in-a-blanket
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: oriental chicken spaghetti
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, prepare thin spaghetti as label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, cut red pepper and cucumber into matchstick-thin strips.
Thinly slice green onion.
Set aside.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix together well; store in container in refrigerator.
Very good for preparing cake pans.

title: creamy pepper dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers for dipping.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.
Do not double recipe.

title: baked french toast
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Lay half of bread on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Mix eggs with milk; add vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over bread slices.
Poke holes in bread with fork so bread will soak up egg mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and heat.
Fill large size tortillas with mixture of the olives, onions, cheese and chicken.
Roll tortillas and place in a baking pan, opening side down.
Pour sauce over tortillas; sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and peanuts in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes; stir.
Microwave for 13 minutes or until syrup separates into threads.
Stir in margarine, soda and vanilla until light and bubbly.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet; spread into a thin layer.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: chunky ham casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package and drain.
Mix together soup, milk, cheese, salt, pepper and ham. Add macaroni and mix well. Pour into buttered dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese lightly.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat until very light.
Add vanilla and lemon extract; blend well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with combined buttermilk and vinegar.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 7 x 10 x 2-inch loaf pan or 2 (8-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake loaf at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Orange Frosting.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables in colander.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup of Swiss cheese.
Stir in the vegetables.
Put into the microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Be sure to cover with wax paper.
Take out of the microwave and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of Swiss cheese and can of Durkee French fried onions.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 3 minutes on High.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: *I prefer to use the low-fat or fat-free cream cheese!

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Pour 1 or 2 cups broth that chicken was cooked in over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: u.m.w.'s cranberry salad for "36"
directions: Dissolve gelatin in first amount of cold water.
Dissolve cherry jello and sugar in hot water.
Add gelatin and stir until all ingredients are thoroughly dissolved.
Coarsely grind cranberries and oranges.
Finely chop apples and celery. Thoroughly mix all ingredients except lettuce and refrigerate in rectangular pans overnight.
Cut into serving squares on lettuce leaf.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Dip each cookie in sweet milk and layer cookies in pan.
Put cool whip between layers.
Can add nuts on top.

title: lemon bar cookies
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice and rind.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, butter or margarine, sugar and oatmeal.
Pat mixture in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan, saving 1/3 mixture for top. Pat firmly.
Pour lemon/condensed milk mixture over cookie mixture.
Pat remaining crumbs on top firmly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares when cool.
Decorate with cherry bits. Store in airtight tin in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and pineapple.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Ice with confectioners icing made with pineapple juice.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick and water until a soft dough.
Pat in an 8 x 8-inch pan, pressing up sides.

title: chicken and yellow rice combo
directions: Combine chicken, badia sazon, seasoning, salt and pepper, cut up bell peppers, onion and drained mixed vegetables (if used); cover with 2 cups water and cook on medium heat until done and there is approximately 1 cup of water remaining in the pot.
Then add 2 cups of rice and 3 cups of water; boil on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Turn heat down to low; cover with lid for 20 more minutes until rice is done.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop by tablespoonful on greased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: broccoli  bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 13 x 9 glass pan for best results.
Its very moist and needs to be baked thin.
Grease pan well and bake for 30 minute at 400°.

title: millet casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Bake
in covered casserole dish for one hour at 350°; or bring to boil on stove top and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: diet cake
directions: Cook together until dry the box of raisins and two cups of water.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: philadelphia cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients until thick and smooth.
Add more confectioners sugar to your desired consistency.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cut sausage in chunks, combine with next four ingredients in large skillet on medium heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in peas and mushrooms. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Simmer covered for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at temperature on package.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing mix; spoon on rolls.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables on dressing and add cheese on top.
Chill for 2 hours; cut in small squares and serve.
You may also cut the squares before adding vegetables because it is easier.

title: easy caramel bars
directions: Thaw but don't raise 2 loaves bread dough.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tear one loaf of dough in pan.
Mix butter, brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon together.
Pour over dough. Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Tear second loaf and place pieces on top of filling.
Let rise at room temperature for 2 1/2 hours. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip crisscross cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls. Press with fork dipped in flour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda together, then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and oats.
Mix well and place in refrigerator until chilled.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts, then roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place approximately 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: ras-cranberry ice
directions: Poach cranberries in water for 10 minutes, then run through sieve with raspberries.
Add Equal and lemon juice; place in 1/2 to 1 cup containers.
Place in freezer until very slushy.
Serve.

title: turkey vegetable noodle soup
directions: Add vegetables to turkey broth along with salt and noodles; simmer 15 minutes.
Add turkey; heat thoroughly and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Combine the ingredients in a casserole dish (except margarine and stuffing).
Combine margarine and stuffing and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Cut cheeses in small pieces; combine in a saucepan with milk. Stir over low heat until cheeses melt.
Stir in wine and crab; heat through.
Serve in chafing dish with Shredded Wheat wafers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into small balls (a little larger than marbles).
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
They will rise and fall just before they finish baking.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with Cool Whip.
Stir in drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup of the mushroom soup, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Cook patties over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Set aside.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining soup mixture and mushrooms in skillet.
Reduce to low.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes until patties are cooked completely through.
tags: cream of mushroom soup mixed with milk

title: beer biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients well, adjusting the sugar according to how sweet a biscuit you want. Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with honey butter.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip; spread on bottom of crust.

title: shrimp souffle
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour until blended. Gradually stir in milk.
Add salt, paprika and curry powder.
When sauce is thick and boiling, stir in shrimp.
Beat well in a separate bowl the egg yolks.
Stir part of the sauce into them. When well blended, pour this mixture into the saucepan.
Stir the sauce over very low heat for a minute to permit the yolks to thicken slightly.
Remove from heat and add Worcestershire sauce. Cool.
Whip egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon salt until stiff.
Fold lightly into the sauce.
Bake in ungreased 9-inch baking dish at 325°.
After 10 minutes increase heat slightly.
Bake until firm for about 35 minutes.

title: simple basic yeast dough - "no kneading"
directions: Add yeast to water; let stand a few minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Combine milk, margarine and sugar; heat to about 120°. Cool; add eggs, salt and 2 cups of flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Blend in remaining flour; beat 5 minutes.
Do not knead.
Brush with shortening.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead 1 minute.
Shape into rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
